天气开始变热的时候，就是她最伤心的季节

174
00:19:38,094 --> 00:19:39,446
As soon as we get her off to Simla
我们会尽快送她去西米拉

175
00:19:39,470 --> 00:19:41,462
she'll be as right as rain, won't you old girl?
她就不会伤心流泪了，对吗，我的老太婆

176
00:19:46,727 --> 00:19:50,471
My mother keeps asking, "Why isn't Anne married?"
我妈妈不停地问我，安妮为什么不结婚？

177
00:19:53,067 --> 00:19:54,478
I don't know what to tell her.
我不知道该怎么回答她

178
00:19:54,985 --> 00:19:56,351
What should I tell her?
我该怎么回答她？

179
00:19:58,572 --> 00:20:01,189
Well, oh well, I can tell you.
哦，好吧，我可以告诉你

180
00:20:02,576 --> 00:20:04,738
I did want to, only...
我之前确实想结婚
181
00:20:05,871 --> 00:20:09,035
the person I was with, he was married
只不过我想嫁的那人是已婚

182
00:20:09,542 --> 00:20:12,501
and he kept saying he was going to get a divorce.
他一直说他会离婚的

183
00:20:13,379 --> 00:20:14,870
Then he finally did...
后来他终于离婚了

184
00:20:16,006 --> 00:20:17,963
only he married someone else.
只不过娶了别人

185
00:20:18,050 --> 00:20:20,508
I mean, someone different, not me.
我的意思是，不是我，是别人

186
00:20:20,594 --> 00:20:23,177
Well, no matter, we'll find you an Indian husband.
没关系，我们会给你找一个印度丈夫的

187
00:20:23,472 --> 00:20:26,135
- Ah.
啊
- A very nice, rich Indian husband.
一个富有的善良的印度男人

188
00:20:26,934 --> 00:20:30,598
And then you can live here and have a lot of Indian children.
这样你就可以留着这里，还会有很多印度宝宝

189
00:20:31,772 --> 00:20:34,435
- Would you like that?
你想要那样吗？
- What, children?
什么，宝宝吗？

190
00:20:34,483 --> 00:20:37,521
No, you know an Indian husband.
不是，你知道的，像我一样的

191
00:20:38,612 --> 00:20:39,648
Someone like me.
印度丈夫

192
00:20:40,948 --> 00:20:42,985
But you think I'm very ugly, don't you?
但你觉得我很丑，是吗？

193
00:20:43,367 --> 00:20:46,405
- Oh, horrible.
哦，不忍直视
- Oh.
哦

194
00:21:00,301 --> 00:21:01,917
Begum Sahib welcomes you.
女王陛下欢迎大家

195
00:21:01,969 --> 00:21:03,835
She is very happy to meet this...
她非常开心能够会见

196
00:21:03,888 --> 00:21:05,379
Angelic girl.
这位天使一般的女孩

197
00:21:05,431 --> 00:21:06,763
- Angelic girl.
天使般的女孩
- Thank you.
谢谢

198
00:21:06,849 --> 00:21:09,432
Mrs Rivers is the wife of our assistant collector,
里弗斯夫人是我们助理收税员的妻子

199
00:21:09,477 --> 00:21:12,891
and we are privileged indeed to have so charming a couple in our midst.
我们非常地荣幸我们当中有这样一对魅力无限的夫妻

200
00:21:13,022 --> 00:21:17,187
The assistant collector...
助理收税员

201
00:21:22,406 --> 00:21:25,114
- Have you been to India before?
你以前来过印度吗？
- No.
没有

202
00:21:25,993 --> 00:21:28,110
This is absolutely my first time,
这是我第一次来印度

203
00:21:28,579 --> 00:21:31,037
and I couldn't be more thrilled.
我非常地激动

204
00:21:38,589 --> 00:21:39,921
How long have you been married?
你结婚多久了？

205
00:21:39,965 --> 00:21:41,206
Six months.
六个月

206
00:21:41,550 --> 00:21:42,791
We were married in England
我们是在英国结的婚

207
00:21:42,843 --> 00:21:45,586
but I only followed my husband out here a few weeks ago.
我只是几周前跟随我的丈夫来到这里的

208
00:21:51,811 --> 00:21:53,143
Any children?
有孩子吗？

209
00:21:53,687 --> 00:21:55,349
We were married in September.
我们九月份才结的婚

210
00:21:59,109 --> 00:22:01,567
She hopes that the durbar wasn't too tiring for you.
她希望你不会很无聊

211
00:22:01,695 --> 00:22:03,903
Oh, I loved every moment of it.
哦， 我享受这里的每时每刻

212
00:22:03,948 --> 00:22:06,486
It looked splendid and was so well done.
皇宫看起来金碧辉煌，尽善尽美

213
00:22:06,867 --> 00:22:09,200
It was thrilling to see your son, the Nawab.
我非常兴奋能见到土邦王，您的儿子

214
00:22:09,245 --> 00:22:11,407
I've always like to hear the Khatam national anthem.
我一直都喜欢听哈塔姆的国歌

215
00:22:11,455 --> 00:22:14,323
You must be terribly proud of him, he's terrifically handsome and...
你肯定非常地骄傲，他真的太帅了

216
00:22:14,375 --> 00:22:16,082
How does it go?
怎么唱来着？

217
00:22:17,336 --> 00:22:20,204
He'd cause a sensation in any London drawing room.
他能在伦敦任何一间会客室引起轰动

218
00:22:54,498 --> 00:22:55,498
Olivia?
奥莉维亚？

219
00:22:59,003 --> 00:23:00,003
Olivia?
奥莉维亚？

220
00:23:15,394 --> 00:23:18,933
You know, they think they're frightfully clever,
你知道吗，他们以为自己聪明非凡

221
00:23:19,773 --> 00:23:21,810
but really they're so transparent.
但事实上，他们太容易被人看穿了

222
00:23:22,026 --> 00:23:23,562
- Who?
谁？
- Indians.
印度人

223
00:23:24,069 --> 00:23:25,069
All of them.
所有的印度人

224
00:23:25,362 --> 00:23:27,604
From our right on up to the Nawab, there.
从我们这里的印度人一直到土邦王那里的印度人

225
00:23:28,365 --> 00:23:29,981
They're like children.
他们就像孩子一样

226
00:23:30,367 --> 00:23:32,154
They look like very grown up men to me,
依我看来，他们都是非常成熟的男人

227
00:23:32,995 --> 00:23:34,486
certainly the Nawab does.
尤其是土邦王

228
00:23:38,208 --> 00:23:39,824
Where's his wife?
他的妻子呢？

229
00:23:40,252 --> 00:23:42,960
Oh, she's not here, she ran away and left him.
她不在这儿，她和别人私奔了，留下他一个人

230
00:23:43,297 --> 00:23:44,583
Oh really? Tell me.
真的吗？跟我说说

231
00:23:44,632 --> 00:23:45,839
Oh, I don't know.
我也不清楚

232
00:23:45,925 --> 00:23:47,541
He eloped with her to Paris.
他们私奔去了巴黎

233
00:23:47,885 --> 00:23:49,922
Her family didn't like it so they broke it up,
但是她的家人不同意，他们就分手了

234
00:23:49,970 --> 00:23:51,256
something of that sort.
差不多就是这样

235
00:23:53,599 --> 00:23:56,057
I say, did you see that new memsahib,
我说，你见到我们新来的人了吗？

236
00:23:56,852 --> 00:23:57,717
did you notice her?
你注意到她了吗？

237
00:23:57,770 --> 00:23:59,386
That tall blonde?
那个高高的金发碧眼的女人？

238
00:23:59,438 --> 00:24:01,100
Oh yes, yes.
哦，见到了，见到了

239
00:24:01,315 --> 00:24:02,959
I thought she was a distinct improvement on the others.
我倒觉得她比其他人的态度有明显的改善

240
00:24:02,983 --> 00:24:04,895
- Not that that's saying much.
虽然不是很多
- HE LAUGHS
呵呵

241
00:24:05,319 --> 00:24:07,982
Listen, I remembered another memsahib joke.
听着，我想起另外一个笑话

242
00:24:08,072 --> 00:24:10,940
It's about this Englishwoman that went to the races in Calcutta.
一个柔美的英国女人去加尔各答的比赛
243
00:24:11,408 --> 00:24:12,819
Her shoelace came undone
她的一只鞋的鞋带松了

244
00:24:12,910 --> 00:24:14,446
and when she bent down to tie it up
当她俯身系鞋带的时候

245
00:24:14,578 --> 00:24:16,535
a jockey came along and plonked a saddle on her.
一名赛马的骑手经过，给了她一鞭子

246
00:24:16,622 --> 00:24:18,830
Exactly, because she looked like a horse.
当然了，因为她看起来像一匹马

247
00:24:18,874 --> 00:24:21,833
And when her friends all asked her, "My dear, whatever did you do?"
而当她的朋友们问她，亲爱的，你到底做了什么？

248
00:24:21,877 --> 00:24:23,834
She said, "What could I do, my dears?"
她回答，亲爱的，我还能做什么呢

249
00:24:24,088 --> 00:24:26,080
"I came third."
我跑了第三名

250
00:24:32,596 --> 00:24:34,303
Oh, I was talking to Beth Crawford today.
今天我和贝丝・克劳福德聊天

251
00:24:34,348 --> 00:24:36,590
Now they're leaving for Simla at the end of next month
她们下个月月底出发去西米拉

252
00:24:36,684 --> 00:24:39,472
so I asked her to book you a berth at the same time
我求她也同时帮你

253
00:24:39,520 --> 00:24:40,556
on the Kalka Mail.
订了一张车票

254
00:24:41,063 --> 00:24:43,271
It's over night but it won't be too bad, I promise you.
虽然要一个晚上，但我向你保证不会很累

255
00:24:43,941 --> 00:24:48,185
Now the journey up to the mountains is another four hours, but what a journey.
爬上山顶还要四个小时，但想想沿途的风景
256
00:24:48,237 --> 00:24:49,237
You'll love it.
你会喜欢的

257
00:24:49,279 --> 00:24:51,271
The scenery, not to mention the changing climate.
那里风景优美，更别提凉爽的天气了

258
00:24:51,907 --> 00:24:54,115
You don't for one moment think I'd go without you?
你不会真的觉得没有你我会自己去吧？

259
00:24:54,493 --> 00:24:56,826
But Beth will be there, and Mary Minnies.
但有贝丝在，还有玛丽・明尼

260
00:24:56,912 --> 00:24:58,390
They'll take care of you.
她们会照顾好你的

261
00:24:58,414 --> 00:25:00,531
Oh, that's just silly Olivia.
真是傻奥莉维亚

262
00:25:01,208 --> 00:25:04,701
Mother spent four months away from father every year, year after year.
妈妈每年都要离开爸爸四个月，就这样年复一年

263
00:25:04,962 --> 00:25:06,999
She didn't like it either but,
她也不喜欢这样生活，但是

264
00:25:07,381 --> 00:25:09,794
when you're in a district that's the way it has to be.
当你管理一个行政区的时候，生活就是这样的

265
00:25:14,972 --> 00:25:17,635
You have no idea how hot it gets.
你难以想象这里会有多热，你会抓狂的

266
00:25:18,308 --> 00:25:19,844
It can drive you mad.
你会很烦躁，
267
00:25:20,811 --> 00:25:23,349
You'll be irritable, we will quarrel over every little thing.
我们会因为一点儿小事就吵架

268
00:25:23,397 --> 00:25:24,683
I'm not going.
我不去

269
00:25:25,858 --> 00:25:28,145
You don't think I like it any better than you do, do you?
你觉得我很想你离开，是吗？

270
00:25:29,194 --> 00:25:30,981
I'll <i>be</i> bored.
我会无聊死的

271
00:25:31,196 --> 00:25:36,191
I'll be hot, irritable, all right, we'll quarrel...
天气会很热，我会很烦躁，我们会吵架，没关系的

272
00:25:38,787 --> 00:25:41,370
but please don't send me away from you.
但请不要让我离开你

273
00:27:36,280 --> 00:27:38,363
I believe you've made a mistake.
我猜您进错房间了

274
00:27:42,703 --> 00:27:44,035
Olivia.
奥莉维亚

275
00:27:44,079 --> 00:27:46,446
Oh, thank goodness darling, are you all right?
谢天谢地，亲爱的，没事吧

276
00:27:47,040 --> 00:27:48,977
Well I sort of got lost and there's so many doors...
我有点儿迷路了，这里门太多了

277
00:27:49,001 --> 00:27:51,709
- ...and they all look exactly the same.
每个门看起来都一样
- Oh, scrumptious.
哦，亲爱的

278
00:28:07,352 --> 00:28:10,561
I felt like Queen Alexandra driving through Hyde Park.
我觉得像亚历山德拉王后开车穿过海德公园

279
00:28:10,898 --> 00:28:14,357
And you give him a coat, or a trouser, or a shirt, or something to copy.
你给他一件大衣，一条裤子，一件衬衫，或者其他的什么去模仿

280
00:28:14,610 --> 00:28:16,977
One way is to get these little lamps the Hindus have,
获得印度教徒手中小灯笼的一种方法是

281
00:28:17,029 --> 00:28:21,069
and you fold them in the leaves, and you sail them on the water,
把他们折在叶子里，让他们在水中漂浮

282
00:28:21,116 --> 00:28:23,278
and then the croc gets intrigued of course,
接着就会把鳄鱼吸引过来

283
00:28:23,327 --> 00:28:26,445
and pops up his head, bang straight in the eye.
它们探出头来，纾直接撞到了眼睛

284
00:28:26,580 --> 00:28:31,450
Eight or nine months later I heard from Cocksons
八九个月后，我听到了这样的对话

285
00:28:31,543 --> 00:28:34,627
that there's a greasy piece of paper with my name on it,
一封有我名字的谄媚信件

286
00:28:34,671 --> 00:28:37,209
it was sitting in the Peshawar bazaar.
出现在集市上

287
00:28:37,716 --> 00:28:40,254
It was said to be worth 50 pounds sterling.
据说价值50英镑

288
00:28:40,761 --> 00:28:42,252
Of course Major Minnies, of course.
当然了，梅杰・明尼，毫无疑问

289
00:28:42,346 --> 00:28:44,759
An Englishman's word and all that sort of thing.
一个英国人的文字，诸如此类的物件

290
00:28:45,057 --> 00:28:47,424
Doesn't his mother ever come to any of his dinner parties?
他妈妈从来不参加他的晚宴吗？
 
291
00:28:47,517 --> 00:28:48,828
How could she, what on Earth are you saying,
你想什么呢，她怎么会

292
00:28:48,852 --> 00:28:51,936
with all these men? Not that generation, never.
和一群男人在一起呢？那代人才不会呢，绝不会

293
00:28:52,272 --> 00:28:56,266
What about his wife? I mean when they still lived together.
他的妻子呢？我是说他们以前一起生活的时候

294
00:28:56,443 --> 00:28:57,809
Oh, you know about that, do you?
你都知道了，不是吗？

295
00:28:58,028 --> 00:29:01,442
Here, try one of these, they're a bit sticky but quite delicious.
来，尝尝这个，有点儿黏，但是非常好吃

296
00:29:01,782 --> 00:29:04,069
Did you know her, what was she like?
你认识她吗？她长的怎么样？

297
00:29:04,117 --> 00:29:05,904
Of course, if it isn't terribly secret.
当然了，如果这不是什么秘密的话

298
00:29:05,994 --> 00:29:08,111
Actually, in a way, it was all my fault.
实际上，某种程度上，都是我的错

299
00:29:08,163 --> 00:29:10,701
She was at school in England with a young cousin of mine,
她在英国上学的时候和我表妹玛乔丽是同学

300
00:29:10,749 --> 00:29:13,207
Marjorie, and I took both the girls to a party
我带她们参加他在卡奇酒店

301
00:29:13,293 --> 00:29:14,625
that he was giving at Claridges.
举办的一个聚会

302
00:29:14,670 --> 00:29:17,287
It was all very thrilling and totally out of bounds for them.
她们都兴奋极了，完全地解放自我

303
00:29:17,464 --> 00:29:19,376
And then they both fell in love with him.
她们两个后来都爱上了他

304
00:29:19,716 --> 00:29:22,459
Poor old Marjorie with her stumpy legs, she never had a chance.
可怜的玛乔丽，两条短粗的腿，一点儿机会都没有

305
00:29:22,552 --> 00:29:26,592
- The other one was very pretty, of course?
看来另外一个非常漂亮了？
- Oh god yes, Sandy was a peach.
天哪，当然了，桑迪太招人喜欢了

306
00:29:26,848 --> 00:29:28,384
She was only 16 at the time.
她当时只有十六岁

307
00:29:28,475 --> 00:29:32,014
Twenty years younger than he was, not that that's what bothered her family.
比他小了二十岁，她家人对此并不忧虑
308
00:29:32,062 --> 00:29:35,681
They were trying to get her married off to a Hyderabad prince who was 30 years older.
当时他们正想方设法让她嫁给一位大她三十岁的海德拉巴王子

309
00:29:35,941 --> 00:29:38,604
Of course, he was a much bigger prince than our Nawab.
当然，比我们土邦王大很多的王子

310
00:29:39,736 --> 00:29:43,025
His wife's family had to come and take her away.
她的妻子的家人不得不过来把她接走

311
00:29:43,490 --> 00:29:45,106
There were rumours of poison.
谣言都是以讹传讹

312
00:29:45,367 --> 00:29:48,360
- Good lord.
天哪
- Some said it was the begum
有些人说是因为女王

313
00:29:48,453 --> 00:29:51,196
because she was jealous of her daughter-in-law.
因为她嫉妒她的儿媳妇

314
00:29:51,331 --> 00:29:54,074
She'd already got rid of his first wife years before.
很多年前，她就除掉了他的第一任妻子

315
00:29:55,043 --> 00:29:58,536
But some said it was the Nawab himself
但有些人说是因为土邦王自己

316
00:29:58,839 --> 00:30:01,047
because he'd fallen in love with a dancing girl.
因为他爱上了一名舞女

317
00:30:02,467 --> 00:30:04,459
Of course, no dancing girl ever materialised
当然，所有的舞女都很现实

318
00:30:04,553 --> 00:30:08,388
so it must've been one of those rumours started by an interested party.
肯定是利益相关方散播了其中一种谣言
319
00:30:08,849 --> 00:30:12,559
It had been Sumerca and Keifer and God knows where,
它曾在上帝才知道的萨玛卡和肯佛尔出现过

320
00:30:12,602 --> 00:30:14,844
it had come over the Khyber pass
最后又来到了卡波尔集市上

321
00:30:14,938 --> 00:30:17,146
and was presented at the Peshawar bazaar
据说，在那个集市上

322
00:30:17,232 --> 00:30:21,397
and was still said to be worth 50 pounds sterling.
这封信仍然价值五十英镑

323
00:30:24,281 --> 00:30:26,523
He's heard that story at least six times.
这个故事他至少听过六次了

324
00:30:26,575 --> 00:30:28,487
So have I and I've only been here three weeks.
我也是，而我来这儿才三周

325
00:30:29,578 --> 00:30:30,805
I don't think I could bear to hear one more anecdote
我觉得我无法忍受再听一个

326
00:30:30,829 --> 00:30:34,493
about what happened in Kabul in 13, don't you know, old chap?
1913年发生在喀布尔的传闻轶事了，老兄，你不知道吗？

327
00:30:34,875 --> 00:30:36,894
Sometimes I think I must be the only person in the world
有时候我觉得我的祖父是世界上唯一一个

328
00:30:36,918 --> 00:30:39,501
whose grandfather was not at the siege of Lucknow.
没有参加勒克瑙起义的人了

329
00:30:39,588 --> 00:30:42,501
- Mine wasn't.
我祖父也没参加
- Douglas's was, of course.
道格拉斯的祖父一定参加了

330
00:30:42,591 --> 00:30:43,957
He said, "Work?"
他说，工作？

331
00:30:44,051 --> 00:30:45,811
"You won't have to work for your first year."
第一年你不需要工作

332
00:30:45,844 --> 00:30:47,322
"Oh by the way, Rivers I've got a..."
对了，里弗斯，我已经

333
00:30:47,346 --> 00:30:49,554
He's very good looking, I like him.
他长的很帅，我很喜欢

334
00:30:49,598 --> 00:30:51,055
Oh, do you?
哦，是吗？

335
00:30:51,099 --> 00:30:54,012
So do I.
我也很喜欢

336
00:30:57,272 --> 00:30:58,808
We were just talking about you.
我们刚刚在谈论你

337
00:30:58,857 --> 00:31:00,519
Nothing about good I assure you.
我向你保证，都是好话

338
00:31:01,401 --> 00:31:05,361
The state of Khatm has always been renowned for its hospitality.
哈塔姆一直以好客闻名
339
00:31:05,739 --> 00:31:08,573
Except in the time of the chap, what's his name?
除了那个家伙的时代，叫什么名字来着？

340
00:31:08,617 --> 00:31:10,483
"Ana" something, Pan.
安娜什么，坎

341
00:31:10,577 --> 00:31:11,943
Amanulla Khan.
阿曼努汗・坎

342
00:31:12,954 --> 00:31:16,288
Oh, Dr Saunders, I hope you're not going to hold that against me?
桑德斯医生，我希望你不要因此对我有敌意

343
00:31:16,583 --> 00:31:18,791
It's not fair Dr Sahib.
萨希卜医生，这不公平

344
00:31:19,127 --> 00:31:20,993
Perhaps Your Excellency has not heard the story
也许阁下没有听过我祖先

345
00:31:21,046 --> 00:31:23,333
of my ancestor and the party he gave?
举办宴会的那个故事？

346
00:31:23,882 --> 00:31:26,090
A neighbouring prince, the raja of Mong,
一位邻国的王子，蒙古的王侯

347
00:31:26,343 --> 00:31:28,801
had done something to displease my ancestor.
做了一些事，惹得我祖先不高兴

348
00:31:29,388 --> 00:31:33,223
So he invited the raja and his retainers to a feast.
因此他设宴邀请这位王子和他的家臣

349
00:31:34,351 --> 00:31:36,434
A ceremonial tent was put up,
宴会的帐篷搭建好了

350
00:31:37,020 --> 00:31:39,057
some choice arrangements were made,
一切都安排妥当

351
00:31:39,773 --> 00:31:42,516
and when the guests were seated to eat and drink
当宾客就座饮酒作乐的时候

352
00:31:42,818 --> 00:31:45,481
to their heart's content, just as we are now,
每个人都心满意足，就像我们现在一样

353
00:31:46,488 --> 00:31:49,481
at that very moment Amanullah Khan
就在这个时候，阿曼努汗・坎

354
00:31:49,783 --> 00:31:52,150
gave a secret sign to his men
给他的手下一个暗号

355
00:31:52,661 --> 00:31:54,698
and they cut the ropes of the tent
他们砍断了帐篷的绳子

356
00:31:54,955 --> 00:31:56,617
so that the raja and his party
因此这位王子和他的宴会

357
00:31:56,957 --> 00:31:59,165
were entangled under the canvas.
困在了帐篷里面

358
00:32:00,419 --> 00:32:02,285
When they were trapped there like animals,
他们像动物一样被困住的时候

359
00:32:02,879 --> 00:32:05,963
Amanullah Khan and his men took their daggers
阿曼努汗・坎和他的手下拿起他们的匕首

360
00:32:06,883 --> 00:32:10,672
and stabbed them through the canvas again and again,
一遍又一遍地插进帐篷里

361
00:32:12,097 --> 00:32:16,011
'til there was not one single enemy left alive.
直到没有一个活口留下来

362
00:32:17,269 --> 00:32:19,431
They still have that tent, Mrs Rivers
里弗斯夫人，他们现在仍保留着那个帐篷

363
00:32:19,729 --> 00:32:21,937
and the blood is so fresh and new
鲜红的血液

364
00:32:21,982 --> 00:32:23,939
it's as if it had only happened yesterday.
仿佛一切发生在昨天

365
00:32:24,025 --> 00:32:26,938
The cause of this enmity was something very small.
这次仇恨的起因是非常小的事情

366
00:32:27,362 --> 00:32:29,024
A trifling, one could say.
可以说是微不足道

367
00:32:30,031 --> 00:32:33,365
The raja had broken his word over a marriage contract,
这位王子违背了婚约

368
00:32:33,618 --> 00:32:36,452
not with Amanullah himself but with one of his followers.
不是和阿曼努汗，而是和阿曼努汗的手下

369
00:32:37,747 --> 00:32:39,033
It was a question of honour
这是名声问题

370
00:32:39,916 --> 00:32:42,750
and Amanullah Khan was not the man to sit quietly
当阿曼努汗・坎或者他的手下被羞辱的时候

371
00:32:42,836 --> 00:32:46,580
when he or anyone of his was insulted.
他绝不会坐视不管

372
00:32:49,342 --> 00:32:52,085
Your Excellency, ladies and gentlemen,
阁下，女士们，先生们

373
00:32:52,679 --> 00:32:53,679
to the King Emperor.
敬英国国王和印度皇帝

374
00:33:28,715 --> 00:33:30,832
- The King Emperor.
敬英国国王和印度皇帝
- The King Emperor.
敬英国国王和印度皇帝


375
00:33:37,015 --> 00:33:39,758
Rivers is going to the village of Rampur in the morning.
里弗斯明早要去兰普尔的一个村庄

376
00:33:39,809 --> 00:33:41,391
They've been threatened with a raid.
一群盗贼威胁要发起袭击

377
00:33:41,478 --> 00:33:43,014
Retaliatory raid.
报复性的袭击

378
00:33:43,063 --> 00:33:46,352
Obviously one of the villagers informed on the gang.
很明显有村民向他们告密

379
00:33:46,483 --> 00:33:48,600
They kill a few people, break arms and legs,
他们杀了一些人，砍断了人们的手臂和双腿

380
00:33:48,652 --> 00:33:50,564
cut off noses, the usual sort of thing,
还有鼻子，诸如此类的

381
00:33:50,695 --> 00:33:52,527
just to show everyone who's who.
就是为了证明他们是谁

382
00:33:52,656 --> 00:33:54,613
And the Nawab gives them his protection?
土邦王保护了他们？

383
00:33:54,699 --> 00:33:56,736
Yes, in return for a share of the loot,
是的，至少我们怀疑交换的条件是

384
00:33:56,826 --> 00:33:58,237
at least that's what we suspect.
分享他们的战利品

385
00:33:58,453 --> 00:34:00,365
He's nothing but a common brigand.
他不过是个普通的强盗

386
00:34:01,248 --> 00:34:04,082
It's just one dash thing after another.
一次又一次的袭击

387
00:34:04,417 --> 00:34:06,704
Ah, but Crawford, that's the definition of our business,
但是克劳福德，这就是我们的机遇

388
00:34:06,836 --> 00:34:08,481
getting out of one dash thing after another.
摆脱一次又一次袭击

389
00:34:09,631 --> 00:34:11,998
What couldn't I give to get out of this one?
我愿意付出一切摆脱这次袭击

390
00:34:12,092 --> 00:34:13,092
Gentlemen.
先生们

391
00:35:27,417 --> 00:35:28,828
What's that singing?
哪儿来的歌声？

392
00:35:28,918 --> 00:35:30,875
It's the entertainment.
是娱乐演出

393
00:35:30,920 --> 00:35:33,412
Oh, do you think it would be all right to go and see?
我过去看看，你觉得可以吗？

394
00:35:34,132 --> 00:35:37,625
Well I suppose so, if you really want to.
如果你真的想去的话，我觉得没问题

395
00:35:38,887 --> 00:35:41,220
These things are supposed to be strictly for men.
这些表演应该是专门为男人准备的

396
00:35:42,140 --> 00:35:43,972
Oh well, go on.
好吧，去吧

397
00:36:18,134 --> 00:36:19,134
Hello.
嗨

398
00:36:21,554 --> 00:36:22,510
Strange music.
奇怪的音乐

399
00:36:22,555 --> 00:36:24,512
- Do you hate it?
你不喜欢吗？
- Heavens no.
天哪，当然不是了

400
00:36:24,766 --> 00:36:26,928
I've just never heard anything like it.
我只是从来没听过这样的音乐

401
00:36:27,018 --> 00:36:29,055
Not a very appreciative audience.
没有一个有鉴赏力的观众

402
00:36:29,688 --> 00:36:32,772
Poor Douglas, he's putting up a great show.
可怜的道格拉斯，你知道，他完全是个乐盲

403
00:36:33,191 --> 00:36:35,979
He's tone deaf you know, utterly.
欣赏不来这场精彩的演出

404
00:36:37,195 --> 00:36:38,606
I have a message for you.
我有个口信给你

405
00:36:39,781 --> 00:36:41,113
Oh yes?
是吗？

406
00:36:41,199 --> 00:36:43,566
As a matter of fact he sent me out to give it to you.
实际上，是他派我出来传口信给你

407
00:36:44,244 --> 00:36:46,782
- But he doesn't even know I exist.
但他都不知道我的存在啊
- Oh doesn't he?
哦，他不知道吗？

408
00:36:46,871 --> 00:36:50,285
He hasn't looked in my direction once, not once all evening.
他整晚都没有往我这个方向看，一次都没有

409
00:36:50,333 --> 00:36:53,792
Well, almost not once anyway, why should he?
好吧，不管怎样，他为什么要往我这个方向看呢？

410
00:36:54,254 --> 00:36:56,166
All the same, he sent me.
他派我出来也是有同样的想法

411
00:36:56,256 --> 00:36:58,498
He wants to invite you and Mr Rivers to dinner next week.
他想邀请你和里弗斯先生下周共进晚餐

412
00:36:58,800 --> 00:37:01,213
Just the two of you, <i>en famille.</i>
只有你们两个

413
00:37:02,011 --> 00:37:03,422
Just Douglas and me?
只有道格拉斯和我吗？

414
00:37:04,097 --> 00:37:07,181
He also wanted me to tell you that it would make him very happy.
他还想让我转告你，他对此非常期待

415
00:37:08,560 --> 00:37:10,222
It would be fun.
会很有趣的

416
00:37:44,846 --> 00:37:47,429
- I have to go.
我得走了
- Oh no.
哦，不行

417
00:37:51,728 --> 00:37:52,728
Please.
求你了

418
00:37:54,439 --> 00:37:55,680
I'll be back in the evening.
我晚上就回来了

419
00:38:00,445 --> 00:38:01,856
In the evening.
要等到晚上啊

420
00:38:05,033 --> 00:38:06,615
Sleep a bit more.
再睡一会儿吧

421
00:38:18,296 --> 00:38:19,296
Douglas?
道格拉斯

422
00:38:30,975 --> 00:38:31,975
Douglas.
道格拉斯

423
00:38:33,520 --> 00:38:35,307
I forgot to tell you something.
我忘记告诉你一件事

424
00:38:36,898 --> 00:38:38,389
What's the matter?
怎么了？

425
00:38:40,401 --> 00:38:42,546
Darling, you wouldn't know, I'm not for a moment blaming you,
亲爱的，你不知道吗，现在我真的不想责备你
426
00:38:42,570 --> 00:38:44,006
but you shouldn't let the servants see you like this.
但你不该让仆人看到你这个样子

427
00:38:44,030 --> 00:38:45,111
See me how?
我怎么了？

428
00:38:47,283 --> 00:38:50,276
I'm as demure as a nun, look.
你看，我穿的像个修女一样保守

429
00:38:50,995 --> 00:38:53,157
Oh, this is too ridiculous.
真是太可笑了

430
00:38:54,707 --> 00:38:56,118
What did you want to tell me?
你刚刚要和我说什么？

431
00:38:56,209 --> 00:38:58,417
The Nawab's invited us to dinner on Wednesday.
土邦王邀请我们周三和他共进晚餐

432
00:38:58,586 --> 00:39:02,296
- Oh no, not again.
不会吧，又来一次
- What do you mean "not again"?
你这是什么意思？

433
00:39:02,340 --> 00:39:04,297
It's the only decent place we've been to.
那是唯一一个我们去过的豪华的地方

434
00:39:04,634 --> 00:39:05,920
At least it's amusing.
至少是有趣的

435
00:39:05,969 --> 00:39:09,553
- Amusing? Gosh.
有趣？天啊
- Well, he wants us, anyway.
不管怎样，反正他邀请了我们

436
00:39:09,639 --> 00:39:11,301
He says he'll send a car and everything.
他说他会派车来接我们并安排好一切

437
00:39:11,391 --> 00:39:13,724
But why should he send a car? We can go with the Crawfords.
他为什么要派车接我们呢？我们可以和克劳福德夫妇一起去

438
00:39:13,810 --> 00:39:16,052
Oh, you don't think they've been invited do you?
你不会觉得他们也被邀请了吧？

439
00:39:16,312 --> 00:39:18,770
Well, he wouldn't ask us without the Crawfords.
没有克劳福德夫妇，他不会邀请我们的

440
00:39:19,399 --> 00:39:21,891
I mean Mr Crawford's the burra sahib, he's my superior.
我的意思是，克劳福德先生，是我的上级

441
00:39:22,318 --> 00:39:24,605
He's also a superior bore.
他也是个超级乏味的人

442
00:39:26,114 --> 00:39:27,946
He wants us, darling,
亲爱的，他只邀请了我们

443
00:39:28,032 --> 00:39:31,366
because we're amusing and nice and they're not.
因为我们有趣又平和，不像克劳德福夫妇

444
00:39:31,619 --> 00:39:35,909
- What, just us, just you and me?
为什么只邀请了我们，我和你？
- Well, why not?
为什么不可以呢？

445
00:39:36,457 --> 00:39:38,949
Why it's most irregular.
因为这完全不合常理

446
00:39:39,460 --> 00:39:42,294
Since when does royalty throw parties for junior officers?
什么时候开始皇室为初级职员举办宴会了？

447
00:39:42,380 --> 00:39:43,746
It's very irregular.
完全不合常理

448
00:39:45,884 --> 00:39:47,671
Oh, God.
哦，天哪

449
00:39:54,767 --> 00:39:56,599
I wish you'd trust me on this.
在这件事上，我希望你能相信我

450
00:39:57,312 --> 00:39:59,645
I really do know best, really I do, darling.
因为我是最了解的，我真的非常了解，亲爱的

451
00:39:59,689 --> 00:40:01,100
You don't know.
你根本就不了解

452
00:40:02,901 --> 00:40:05,814
When you're gone, there's nothing, there's nobody.
你上班之后，这里什么都没有，空空荡荡的

453
00:40:06,654 --> 00:40:08,771
My goodness, the days are long.
天哪，每天都过得特别慢

454
00:40:09,532 --> 00:40:11,444
I never knew days could be so long.
我从来没觉得日子会这么慢

455
00:40:12,785 --> 00:40:15,027
I know it's difficult for you, darling,
亲爱的，我知道这一切对你来说很困哪

456
00:40:15,955 --> 00:40:18,072
but it's all just because it's all so new.
但这全都是因为你在一个全新的环境中

457
00:40:18,625 --> 00:40:22,289
As a matter of fact I was talking about this very thing to Beth Crawford.
实际上，我还和贝丝・克劳福德说过这件事

458
00:40:23,421 --> 00:40:26,630
And you mustn't think that way about Beth, she's a good sort.
你千万别生贝丝的气，她是好意

459
00:40:27,258 --> 00:40:31,719
And do you know what she said? She said that, well, someone as sensitive
你知道她说了什么吗？她说像你这样既敏感

460
00:40:31,763 --> 00:40:33,504
and as intelligent as you,
又聪明的人

461
00:40:34,557 --> 00:40:36,469
see she does appreciate you...
看，她是在夸赞你

462
00:40:37,268 --> 00:40:41,433
well, that you'd surely be all right here,
你在这里完全没问题的

463
00:40:41,731 --> 00:40:43,643
but you, and this is what she said,
而你，这也是她说的

464
00:40:43,691 --> 00:40:47,856
that you'd "come to feel about India just as we do".
你对印度的感觉慢慢的会和我们一样

465
00:40:49,697 --> 00:40:53,361
I know it's easy for me, I have my work.
我知道，这对我来说很简单，因为我有工作

466
00:40:54,369 --> 00:40:56,326
I'm really not fit for anything else.
但其他的事情我也不适应

467
00:40:58,164 --> 00:40:59,516
But you're worth a jolly sight more
与其只做我这个家伙的妻子，你值得

468
00:40:59,540 --> 00:41:01,623
than to be just the wife of a chap like me.
更多美好的东西

469
00:41:03,044 --> 00:41:04,410
I should say so.
我应该这么说

470
00:41:11,469 --> 00:41:12,755
I do love you.
我真的很爱你

471
00:41:18,851 --> 00:41:20,342
See you tonight.
晚上见

472
00:41:21,854 --> 00:41:23,516
I may not be here.
我也许不在家

473
00:41:24,482 --> 00:41:27,225
If it gets too boring I'll run away.
如果太无聊了，我就逃走

474
00:42:48,274 --> 00:42:51,017
- I'll play blind.
我要盲打
- Playing blind?
玩儿盲牌？

475
00:42:51,069 --> 00:42:52,605
All right one, two.
好了，一，二

476
00:42:54,363 --> 00:42:56,730
- Yes, you have to show your cards...
是的，你要亮出你的牌
- Show? One.
亮出来吗？

477
00:42:58,659 --> 00:42:59,991
There you are.
这是怎么回事 我赢了

478
00:43:00,036 --> 00:43:02,014
You cheated me.
你骗了我

479
00:43:02,038 --> 00:43:03,870
Honestly, I didn't see your cards.
他肯定作弊了  老实讲，我都没看见你的牌

480
00:43:05,875 --> 00:43:06,991
One, two.
一，二

481
00:43:14,383 --> 00:43:17,217
So this is how you spend your time, you idle fellow...
无聊的家伙，你就是这样打发时间的

482
00:43:17,303 --> 00:43:19,364
- ...playing cards with women?
和女人打牌？
- I'm not playing anymore.
我再也不玩儿了

483
00:43:19,388 --> 00:43:21,300
I've never seen such abdominal cheating.
我从来没见过用肚子作弊的

484
00:43:24,685 --> 00:43:28,144
- You're her own dear son.
你就像是她的亲生儿子
- If I am your own dear son,
如果我是您亲生的儿子

485
00:43:28,231 --> 00:43:30,188
you shouldn't be cheating me like this.
您刚刚就不该那样作弊

486
00:43:30,608 --> 00:43:33,396
Cheating, not I.
作弊？我，没有

487
00:43:33,444 --> 00:43:35,902
- Pay your debts.
快还钱吧
- Come on, Harry, pay up.
快点儿，哈里，把钱都还上

488
00:43:35,947 --> 00:43:38,314
All gentlemen pay their gambling debts.
绅士都会还清自己的赌债

489
00:43:38,658 --> 00:43:40,695
What would they say in the club?
他们会在俱乐部里说什么？

490
00:43:40,743 --> 00:43:42,826
And what would our Mr Crawford say,
我们的克罗弗德先生会说什么

491
00:43:43,037 --> 00:43:44,744
the esteemed burra sahib?
尊敬的

492
00:43:44,872 --> 00:43:47,080
And what about our esteemed sahib, Mr Rivers?
还有我们尊敬的里弗斯先生会说什么？

493
00:43:47,166 --> 00:43:50,785
Oh, here, I've got this courteous note from Mr Rivers.
对了，这是里弗斯先生给我的答谢函

494
00:44:51,856 --> 00:44:56,567
We've left Satipur, all this is his great state of Khatm.
我们已经离开了赛提普，这都是他统治的哈塔姆的领土

495
00:44:57,195 --> 00:44:59,733
Yes, we've left British India.
是的，我们已经离开了英国统治的印度

496
00:45:00,573 --> 00:45:03,316
Now you're in my power, like him.
现在你和他一样都在我的统治下

497
00:45:04,493 --> 00:45:08,077
I'm only joking.
我只是在开玩笑

498
00:45:09,373 --> 00:45:11,990
I had to go with them, I couldn't not.
我不得不和他一起走，我不能拒绝他

499
00:45:12,084 --> 00:45:14,326
He said he'd be so terribly hurt if I didn't,
他说，如果我不来，如果我再一次拒绝他的邀请

500
00:45:14,378 --> 00:45:16,916
if I refused his invitation again.
他会非常的伤心

501
00:45:55,962 --> 00:45:58,124
Look at him, Mrs Rivers.
看看他，里弗斯太太

502
00:45:59,048 --> 00:46:00,442
What sort of an Englishman are you?
你算是什么英国人呢

503
00:46:00,466 --> 00:46:02,799
One who can't stand your goddamn climate.
不能忍受你的这种鬼天气的英国人

504
00:46:02,927 --> 00:46:06,546
My climate?
我的天气？
Well, Mrs Rivers can stand it very well.
里弗斯太太却适应的很好

505
00:46:07,390 --> 00:46:10,758
Oh dear, dear, Mrs Rivers, what shall we do with him?
亲爱的，亲爱的里弗斯太太，我们该拿他怎么办呢？

506
00:46:11,435 --> 00:46:13,643
He's letting down the side.
他真让人失望

507
00:46:14,188 --> 00:46:16,145
That's not a proper Englishman.
不是个像样的英国人

508
00:46:16,607 --> 00:46:19,224
Do you know what I think? I think he's a very improper Englishman.
你知道我在想什么吗？我想他是个非常不像样的英国人

509
00:46:22,071 --> 00:46:23,071
Here.
给

510
00:46:27,118 --> 00:46:29,781
This place is sacred to the memory of Baba Firdaus,
这圣坛是为了纪念巴巴・阿弗道斯

511
00:46:30,371 --> 00:46:31,371
a holy man.
一位虔诚的圣人

512
00:46:32,123 --> 00:46:34,911
It was built in his honour by my ancestor Amanullah Khan.
我的祖先阿曼努汗・坎建此圣坛表示对他的敬意

513
00:46:34,959 --> 00:46:37,292
Oh, the one you told that frightful story about
哦，你讲的那个把所有客人困在帐篷里

514
00:46:37,336 --> 00:46:40,829
who trapped all his guests in a tent and had them stabbed.
并刺杀了所有人的恐怖故事

515
00:46:41,716 --> 00:46:44,333
You... You call that frightful do you?
你觉得很恐怖，是吗？

516
00:46:45,261 --> 00:46:46,718
I suppose you're right.
我想你是对的

517
00:46:47,430 --> 00:46:50,173
Baba Firdaus gave him shelter here after battle.
战后巴巴・阿弗道斯就在此定居

518
00:46:50,516 --> 00:46:52,553
That's why he built this shrine in gratitude.
这也是他把圣坛建在这儿的原因

519
00:46:52,935 --> 00:46:55,643
He never forgot a friend or an enemy.
他从不会忘记一个敌人或者一个朋友

520
00:46:56,105 --> 00:46:57,385
The British liked him very much.
英国人都非常喜欢他

521
00:46:58,816 --> 00:47:01,479
- I think you like such people, don't you?
我觉得你也喜欢这样的人，不是吗？
- We do?
是吗？

522
00:47:01,652 --> 00:47:04,235
Yes, you know, rough people that fight well,
是的，你知道的，粗鲁的人都善战

523
00:47:04,405 --> 00:47:07,864
mostly on a horse, but best of all, you like the horse.
大多时候都在马背上，但最重要的是你喜欢马

524
00:47:09,410 --> 00:47:12,528
But you're not like that. You don't like the horses, do you?
但你不喜欢那样，你不喜欢骑马，对吧？

525
00:47:12,830 --> 00:47:14,241
You're right, I don't.
你说的对，我不喜欢

526
00:47:14,832 --> 00:47:17,074
You see how well I read your character?
你看我多了解你

527
00:47:34,310 --> 00:47:36,222
Thank you, thank you.
谢谢你，谢谢

528
00:47:46,572 --> 00:47:48,063
Well done.
漂亮

529
00:48:04,048 --> 00:48:06,836
Olivia never told Douglas about the Nawab's picnic.
奥莉维亚从来没跟道格拉斯提起和土邦王野餐的事

530
00:48:07,593 --> 00:48:09,801
She had meant to as soon as she got home,
她一回到家，就打算告诉道格拉斯

531
00:48:10,179 --> 00:48:11,841
but it so happened that he'd been held up
但碰巧那天，集市上发生刺杀事件

532
00:48:11,889 --> 00:48:14,506
by a stabbing incident in the bazaar that day
他脱不开身

533
00:48:14,600 --> 00:48:16,432
and was even later than usual.
比平时回来的晚

534
00:48:16,894 --> 00:48:19,762
She never did get around to telling him about her day.
她一直没有机会把那天的事情告诉道格拉斯

535
00:48:19,814 --> 00:48:21,897
And when he left next morning, she was still asleep.
当第二天早上他离开的时候，她还在睡觉

536
00:48:23,109 --> 00:48:26,102
So instead, she wrote the first of those long,
因此，她写下了第一篇非常长的
537
00:48:26,153 --> 00:48:28,440
really intimate letters to Marcia.
秘密信件给玛西亚

538
00:49:19,081 --> 00:49:21,824
Inder Lal's family always comes to the annual religious festival
英德尔・拉尔的家人经常参加在土邦王的祖先，阿曼努汗・坎

539
00:49:21,876 --> 00:49:25,415
at the tomb built by Amanullah Khan, the Nawab's ancestor.
建造的圣坛的一年一度的宗教节日

540
00:49:26,297 --> 00:49:29,165
Amanullah Khan built the shrine for a Muslim saint,
阿曼努汗・坎建此圣坛是为了纪念一位穆斯林圣人

541
00:49:29,717 --> 00:49:32,710
but now it's a sacred place for both Hindus and Muslims.
但现在这个神圣的地方既属于印度教徒也属于穆斯林教徒

542
00:49:33,179 --> 00:49:36,968
That's the way things happen in India, everything gets mixed up and absorbed.
在印度很多事情都是这样的，开始融合并相互吸引

543
00:49:43,481 --> 00:49:46,565
"Shadi", "shadi", meaning marriage,
沙迪，沙迪，是婚姻的意思

544
00:49:46,859 --> 00:49:48,316
that's what they keep asking me.
也是她们一直问我的问题

545
00:49:50,196 --> 00:49:51,778
"Why aren't you married?"
你为什么还不结婚？

546
00:49:52,031 --> 00:49:55,320
"How come you don't have a husband? No children?"
你怎么能没有丈夫和孩子呢？

547
00:49:55,409 --> 00:49:56,945
"How can you live like that?"
你怎么生活呢？

548
00:50:00,331 --> 00:50:03,290
I told them why don't you find someone really nice for me?
我告诉她们，你们为什么不帮我找一个好人呢？

549
00:50:03,501 --> 00:50:06,289
So they asked Maji to provide a candidate.
因此她们请玛姬挑选一个候选人

550
00:50:07,755 --> 00:50:11,169
Maji's a sort of wise woman whom everyone consults about their problems.
玛姬是个聪明的女人，每个人有问题都会请教她

551
00:50:11,884 --> 00:50:15,093
She said "God would provide", which is her usual response.
通常她都会说，上帝会给她指派的

552
00:51:27,626 --> 00:51:29,913
Maji said Lilavati had been coming here
玛姬说，三十年来莉拉瓦蒂

553
00:51:29,962 --> 00:51:31,544
every year, for 30 years.
每年都会来这儿乞讨

554
00:51:32,089 --> 00:51:34,797
Once she'd been a farmer's wife but her husband died
她以前是个农民的妻子，后来丈夫去世

555
00:51:34,883 --> 00:51:36,670
and her in-laws wouldn't keep her
公婆不要她了

556
00:51:36,760 --> 00:51:38,422
so she began to beg for her living.
因此她开始以乞讨为生

557
00:51:38,887 --> 00:51:41,721
She goes round to all the pilgrim spots because that's where people
她去到各种朝圣的地方，因为在那些地方

558
00:51:41,765 --> 00:51:43,427
are most disposed to be charitable.
人们最愿意施舍了

559
00:51:43,475 --> 00:51:46,058
Giving to the poor is one way of accumulating a good record
施舍穷人是一种积德的方式

560
00:51:46,103 --> 00:51:48,140
so as not to have to be born again.
这样就不必经历重生了

561
00:52:02,578 --> 00:52:04,945
This water is incredibly cold.
这里的水非常的凉

562
00:52:05,956 --> 00:52:07,367
It's always like that.
一直都这么凉的

563
00:52:07,416 --> 00:52:09,311
How do you know, have you been here before?
你怎么知道的，你以前来过这里吗？

564
00:52:09,335 --> 00:52:11,543
I read it somewhere. Are you an American?
我在某处读到的，你是美国人吗？

565
00:52:13,714 --> 00:52:14,830
Canadian?
加拿大人？

566
00:52:16,133 --> 00:52:17,590
I'm not anything now.
现在我哪儿人也不是

567
00:52:17,676 --> 00:52:18,676
I've taken sanyas.
我已经接受涅

568
00:52:18,761 --> 00:52:20,196
That means you strip off everything,
也就是说我脱离了一切

569
00:52:20,220 --> 00:52:23,213
your hair, your clothes, all your personal possessions
头发，衣服，所有的私人财产

570
00:52:23,557 --> 00:52:25,640
and your identity.
还有自我

571
00:52:26,143 --> 00:52:28,351
It's all burned up on a funereal pyre.
一切都在火堆里烧掉了

572
00:52:29,688 --> 00:52:33,022
So it's like dying as a material being
就像是生理上死去了

573
00:52:33,108 --> 00:52:35,145
and being reborn spiritually.
精神上重生了

574
00:52:46,330 --> 00:52:47,662
And what about you?
说说你吧

575
00:52:48,248 --> 00:52:50,956
- I'm doing some research.
我在做调研
- What, on your PhD?
什么，你是博士吗？

576
00:52:52,419 --> 00:52:54,957
For myself, like you.
是为了我自己，和你一样

577
00:52:55,547 --> 00:52:58,540
I'm not researching Hinduism, I've become a Hindu.
我不是在调研印度，而是成为了一名印度教徒

578
00:53:01,178 --> 00:53:04,592
Actually, research was what I used to do in England,
实际上，调研是我在英国做的事情

579
00:53:04,640 --> 00:53:06,347
it was my job, I worked with the BBC.
我和BBC合作，那就是我的工作

580
00:53:06,892 --> 00:53:08,884
And you didn't find it all that fulfilling either?
你从中没有找到成就感？

581
00:53:09,269 --> 00:53:10,885
You wouldn't be here if you did.
否则你也不会在这儿了

582
00:53:14,483 --> 00:53:16,600
I gave it ，I gave it all up...
我放弃了，放弃了一切

583
00:53:19,071 --> 00:53:20,528
because it wasn't reality.
因为一切都不是真实的

584
00:53:21,740 --> 00:53:23,106
I even gave up my name.
我甚至放弃了自己的名字

585
00:53:23,617 --> 00:53:26,075
My guru gave me a new one, Chidananda.
我的古鲁领袖给了我一个新名字 奇德阿南达

586
00:53:26,161 --> 00:53:28,198
- Chid.
奇德
- Ananda.
阿南达

587
00:53:28,664 --> 00:53:31,327
- Chidananda.
奇德阿南达
- It means bliss of mind.
代表精神的幸福

588
00:53:32,710 --> 00:53:34,201
But you can just call me Chid.
但你可以叫我奇德

589
00:53:35,170 --> 00:53:36,286
Chid.
奇德

590
00:53:37,339 --> 00:53:38,830
Are you coming in?
你要下来吗？

591
00:53:48,058 --> 00:53:50,175
- Oh it's nice.
真清澈
- Hm, very nice.
非常清澈

592
00:53:58,110 --> 00:54:00,477
You can't have any money or anything, just this.
你不能带钱和任何东西，只有这个

593
00:54:00,946 --> 00:54:03,654
People have to give you food or anything that you need.
人们才会给你食物或者其他你需要的东西

594
00:54:10,956 --> 00:54:12,618
One rupee is good?
一卢比够吗？

595
00:54:16,295 --> 00:54:17,502
Two.
两张票

596
00:55:02,758 --> 00:55:04,590
You've got a lot of room here.
你住的地方房间挺多

597
00:55:09,056 --> 00:55:12,220
Just for a couple of days, for a little rest.
我就在这儿停留几天，休息一下

598
00:55:14,561 --> 00:55:17,269
All right, all right, but just two days.
好吧，好吧，就两天

599
00:55:17,314 --> 00:55:19,021
I'll show you where.
我带你去你住的地方

600
00:55:40,420 --> 00:55:41,501
Nice.
舒服

601
00:55:41,922 --> 00:55:44,756
It's the light around our body that controls our mind.
我们身体周围的光控制着我们的思想

602
00:55:46,260 --> 00:55:50,004
A pure unharmful mind is a place of perfect happiness.
拥有纯洁善良的思想就得到了真正的幸福

603
00:55:59,523 --> 00:56:00,809
- Light.
光？
- Light?
光？

604
00:56:35,809 --> 00:56:38,142
Whoa, all right come over.
好了，快过来

605
00:56:40,188 --> 00:56:41,269
No, no, no, no.
不，不，不

606
00:56:54,536 --> 00:56:56,323
By the way, when are you leaving?
对了，你打算什么时候离开？

607
00:56:56,872 --> 00:56:58,204
They want me to stay.
他们希望我留下来

608
00:56:58,540 --> 00:57:01,624
Do you even know how poor these people are?
你知道这些人有多穷吗？

609
00:57:02,169 --> 00:57:04,161
They can't afford to feed you.
他们养不起你的

610
00:57:05,255 --> 00:57:07,542
They like it, they like giving.
他们喜欢这样了，喜欢给予

611
00:57:07,758 --> 00:57:10,922
By giving they're taking good karma for their next reincarnation.
今生施舍给予，来生才能结善缘
612
00:57:11,553 --> 00:57:14,261
So you're helping them to a better time in the next life
这么说你在这儿白吃白喝是帮助他们

613
00:57:14,306 --> 00:57:16,673
by eating their food in this one?
来世投个好胎？

614
00:57:19,102 --> 00:57:20,934
I used to be just like you, once.
我以前就和你一样

615
00:57:21,855 --> 00:57:24,063
I wanted materialistic power.
我想要物质上的满足

616
00:57:27,444 --> 00:57:29,310
I was fascinated with power.
我完全沉迷于这种满足感

617
00:57:29,571 --> 00:57:31,007
I went to the library and got all these books
我去图书馆读了很多

618
00:57:31,031 --> 00:57:34,820
on Julius Caesar and Octavius Augustus, those sort of people.
关于奥古斯都・凯撒和盖乌斯・屋大维这类人的书籍

619
00:57:35,077 --> 00:57:37,239
I figured that today's equivalent is big business,
我发现体现在当今社会的等价物就是

620
00:57:37,287 --> 00:57:39,870
big multinational corporations.
跨国集团的大生意

621
00:57:41,208 --> 00:57:44,121
You know I tried to get in on an IBM training course one time,
你知道吗，有一次我曾经参加一场美国国际商用机器公司的培训

622
00:57:44,836 --> 00:57:46,247
but my grades weren't good enough,
但我的成绩不够优秀

623
00:57:46,338 --> 00:57:48,250
and they said that I was crazy,
他们说我疯了

624
00:57:48,840 --> 00:57:50,672
and they sent me to the hospital.
把我送进了医院

625
00:57:55,472 --> 00:57:57,134
That's a tazkiyah procession.
这是游行队伍

626
00:57:58,475 --> 00:58:01,559
It took me a long time to realise that what the Romans had was limited power
我花了很长时间才意识到罗马人拥有的是有限的满足

627
00:58:01,937 --> 00:58:06,477
and that the only unlimited power is what they had in the Vedanta.
而唯一不受限的满足就是不断和精神世界融合

628
00:58:07,693 --> 00:58:10,902
You see, materialistic power is limited.
你要明白物质上的满足是有限的

629
00:58:11,488 --> 00:58:15,778
Real power is absolute, unlimited and undefined.
真正的满足是完全不受限且不明确的

630
00:58:18,745 --> 00:58:20,828
You see, you must be independent in your thinking.
你知道的，你必须要独立思考

631
00:58:21,790 --> 00:58:23,372
But back home they're afraid of that.
但回到现实，他们对此很害怕

632
00:58:23,875 --> 00:58:26,913
Afraid that you might overthrow their power structure.
害怕你推翻他们的满足体系

633
00:58:28,046 --> 00:58:29,662
So they say you're crazy...
所以他们才会说你疯了
634
00:58:31,008 --> 00:58:32,374
put you in a hospital.
把你送进医院

635
00:59:06,960 --> 00:59:08,872
What are you doing？
你在做什么？

636
00:59:08,920 --> 00:59:11,162
I'm just looking.  Drop those things .  there's no harm in looking.
我只是看一下  快放下      看看又不会怎么样

637
00:59:11,256 --> 00:59:13,484
You shouldn't be looking through other people's things like that.
你不应该这样翻看别人的信件

638
00:59:13,508 --> 00:59:15,249
- Absolutely.
当然
- Just throw it all out.
把它们都扔掉

639
00:59:15,302 --> 00:59:16,418
I'll throw <i>you</i> out!
我要把你扔出去

640
00:59:16,511 --> 00:59:17,739
If I ever catch you going through my things again
如果我再抓到你翻看我的东西

641
00:59:17,763 --> 00:59:21,928
I'll throw you out, beads and bangles, begging bowl and all.
我就把你扔出去，你的念珠，手镯，化缘钵，所有的东西都扔出去

642
00:59:23,602 --> 00:59:25,468
Let go of me.
放开我
You know I'm surprised at you.
你知道吗，我还挺惊讶的

643
00:59:25,520 --> 00:59:27,933
I wasn't going through your papers, I was looking for money.
我没打算偷看你的信件，我是在找钱

644
00:59:28,523 --> 00:59:31,436
- Money, what do you need money for?
钱？你要钱做什么？
- Well, you want me to go.
你不是想让我离开吗？不是吗？

645
00:59:31,485 --> 00:59:34,193
You live free, you eat free, you beg in the streets.
你吃住都不需要钱，你还上街乞讨

646
00:59:34,279 --> 00:59:35,440
Don't touch.
不许碰

647
00:59:38,366 --> 00:59:39,698
I know what you think.
我知道你怎么想的

648
00:59:40,660 --> 00:59:42,572
You think you're Olivia, her reincarnation.
你认为你就是奥莉维亚，她的来世

649
00:59:44,164 --> 00:59:46,872
You've seen the photos of her. How could I ever be her?
你看过她的照片了，我怎么可能是她呢？

650
00:59:47,459 --> 00:59:50,418
Anyway, where would I ever find a Nawab
不管怎样，如果我需要一个土邦王

651
00:59:50,462 --> 00:59:53,330
even if I needed one, I mean if I wanted one.
我要去哪儿找呢？我是说当我真的需要的时候

652
00:59:53,381 --> 00:59:55,623
I know what you need, you need sex.
我知道你需要什么，你需要性爱

653
00:59:56,927 --> 00:59:58,008
You mean <i>you</i> do.
你是说你需要吧
 
654
00:59:58,428 --> 01:00:00,670
Why don't you get out of here?
你为什么不离开这里？

655
01:00:00,722 --> 01:00:01,838
I can't help it.
我也情不自禁

656
01:00:01,890 --> 01:00:03,826
It gets to this enormous size, do you want to see?
它就变得这么大了，你想看看吗？

657
01:00:03,850 --> 01:00:04,966
No, I don't.
不，不想

658
01:00:05,060 --> 01:00:06,913
It's due to the mediation, I mean that's a fact,
这是因为冥想的原因，但这是事实

659
01:00:06,937 --> 01:00:09,930
I get charged up with this terrific voltage.
