660
01:00:09,981 --> 01:00:12,018
No, don't laugh, it's a liability.
不，不要笑，你要对我负责

661
01:00:12,067 --> 01:00:14,354
Now come on, Anne.
来吧，安妮
Ow, ow.
喔，喔

662
01:00:55,068 --> 01:00:56,068
Psst.
嘘

663
01:00:57,112 --> 01:00:58,774
Psst, Anne, Anne?
嘘，安妮，安妮？

664
01:01:17,340 --> 01:01:20,549
You're cutting yourself off from the real love experience.
你在切断自己与真爱之间的联系

665
01:01:20,886 --> 01:01:25,051
It's not just sex, it's a union with all life.
这不仅仅是性，这是所有生命的结合

666
01:01:27,767 --> 01:01:30,430
The sexual drive is towards the ultimate orgasm.
性冲动是导向终极高潮的

667
01:01:31,396 --> 01:01:35,140
That ultimate union rising up through the chakras
通过脉轮导向终极纽带

668
01:01:35,192 --> 01:01:37,775
to the third eye, the pineal gland.
导向第三只眼睛，松果体

669
01:01:39,279 --> 01:01:42,147
Explosion of light at the top of the skull.
在头顶形成光

670
01:01:42,991 --> 01:01:47,452
An out of sight, spaced out, super consciousness.
超越视线，魂飞天外，醍醐灌顶

671
01:01:50,874 --> 01:01:52,285
Jesus Christ.
上帝啊

672
01:01:55,629 --> 01:01:58,246
You've got to get in touch with your own femininity, Anne.
你必须激发你自己的女性气质

673
01:02:00,383 --> 01:02:02,545
With your own inner space.
拥有自己的内心世界


674
01:02:54,813 --> 01:02:58,523
What do you think about me taking her to a doctor
你觉得我带她看医生

675
01:02:58,608 --> 01:03:01,021
who specialises in this sort of thing?
治疗这种病的专家，怎么样？

676
01:03:01,111 --> 01:03:03,819
You only get well if you believe in something, Anne.
阿妮，拥有信仰一切才会变好

677
01:03:04,114 --> 01:03:06,527
What do you mean like that, what's going on in there?
你这话是什么意思，里面是怎么回事？

678
01:03:07,075 --> 01:03:08,566
Laugh at us if you wish.
你想嘲笑我们的话，请随便

679
01:03:08,660 --> 01:03:11,949
Oh, no, no, I wouldn't laugh at you. I mean how can, why should I?
哦，不，不，我没有嘲笑你，我的意思是，我怎么会，为什么会嘲笑你们呢？

680
01:03:12,414 --> 01:03:17,205
It's just I think it's worth trying a different form of treatment.
我只是觉得尝试一种不同的治疗方式也未尝不可

681
01:03:17,294 --> 01:03:18,785
I think I should take her to Delhi.
我觉得我应该带她去德里

682
01:03:18,837 --> 01:03:21,921
- There must be doctors there who...
那里一定有医生
- You mean a psychiatrist?
你是说精神病医生吗？

683
01:03:22,841 --> 01:03:25,925
- Who asked you?
谁问你了？
- Don't listen to her.
不要听她的

684
01:03:26,094 --> 01:03:27,630
Psychiatrists are gross.
精神病医生都是庸医

685
01:03:27,846 --> 01:03:30,384
Stay out of this, I'm talking to Inder Lal.
你别插嘴，我在和英德尔・拉尔说话

686
01:03:30,432 --> 01:03:33,391
I'm telling you, I know.
我告诉你，我最了解

687
01:03:34,936 --> 01:03:37,644
Let's just try, I mean I'll...
咱们就去试一试，我的意思是我会……

688
01:03:45,697 --> 01:03:48,360
I think it's just worth trying, me taking her there.
我觉得让我带她去德里试一试是很值得的

689
01:03:48,408 --> 01:03:50,991
Look there's no need, we've made other arrangements.
听我说，不必了，我们已经做了其他的安排

690
01:03:51,161 --> 01:03:53,244
Have you, what sort of arrangements?
是吗？什么安排？

691
01:03:53,288 --> 01:03:57,578
Well, we're going to a pilgrimage to Amarnath.
我们要去阿玛尔纳特朝拜

692
01:03:57,667 --> 01:03:58,828
Mother wants to go.
妈妈想去

693
01:03:58,877 --> 01:04:00,459
- A pilgrimage?
去朝拜？
- Yeah.
是的

694
01:04:00,503 --> 01:04:03,416
But what... Oh gosh, oh dear.
可是，天哪，天哪

695
01:04:03,465 --> 01:04:07,800
They all say this must be done and if I say no they will blame me for it.
他们都同意去朝拜，如果我不同意，他们会因此责怪我的

696
01:04:07,886 --> 01:04:11,175
Look do give him something. And then there's this man behind.
听我说，给他一些东西吧，还有后面的这个人

697
01:04:11,222 --> 01:04:12,963
Please give him something.
请给他一些东西吧

698
01:04:13,600 --> 01:04:16,058
You know, some yogis can actually take their intestines out
你知道吗，一些瑜伽信徒真的会把他们的肠子拿出来

699
01:04:16,102 --> 01:04:19,015
wash them, clean them and put them back in, all nice and clean.
清洗，清洗干净后再完好无损地放回去

700
01:04:19,105 --> 01:04:21,222
How disgusting.
真恶心

701
01:04:23,068 --> 01:04:25,212
I've never seen anyone like you for telling other people
我从来没见过像你这样的人，告诉别人

702
01:04:25,236 --> 01:04:27,398
that their ideas and philosophies are disgusting.
他们的思想和信仰是恶心的

703
01:04:27,822 --> 01:04:30,155
What good are philosophies and ideas when someone's sick?
当人生病的时候，思想和信仰有什么用呢？

704
01:04:30,408 --> 01:04:33,901
All they can come up with to help her is to take her on a pilgrimage.
他们能想出来的帮她的办法就是带她去朝圣

705
01:04:34,162 --> 01:04:35,494
That's right, and I'm going to.
对，我也会去

706
01:04:35,538 --> 01:04:37,538
We're going up to Amarnath to see the Shiva Lingam.
我们要爬上阿玛尔纳特看辛格里诺

707
01:04:37,749 --> 01:04:38,910
Other nostril.
另外一个鼻孔

708
01:04:39,250 --> 01:04:41,412
What's that, Shiva's prick?
那是什么？希瓦的咒锥吗？

709
01:04:41,961 --> 01:04:43,327
Yeah something like that.
是的，差不多吧

710
01:04:43,880 --> 01:04:47,123
It's an object of Hindu worship for women from the day they are born.
从女人出生的那天开始，印度教徒朝奉女人的圣物

711
01:04:47,884 --> 01:04:49,045
Now breathe.
现在深呼吸

712
01:04:49,677 --> 01:04:50,838
It's eight feet tall.
它有八英尺高

713
01:04:50,887 --> 01:04:52,298
You should come with us, Anne.
安妮，你应该和我们一起去

714
01:04:56,017 --> 01:04:57,883
<i>It's more than 50 years ago,</i>
尽管是五十多年前

715
01:04:58,436 --> 01:05:01,304
<i>but I'll never forget the dust storms we had that year.</i>
但我绝不会忘记那一年我们遭遇的沙尘暴

716
01:05:02,482 --> 01:05:05,316
<i>They blew all day, they blew all night.</i>
日夜不停地吹

717
01:05:06,403 --> 01:05:08,065
<i>If you left a chink open anywhere</i>
假如你在某个地方留了一个缝隙

718
01:05:08,113 --> 01:05:11,481
<i>within seconds there would be a fume of dust over everything.</i>
所有的东西马上就盖上了一层灰尘

719
01:05:12,534 --> 01:05:15,277
<i>It got in your eyes, your nostrils,</i>
你的眼睛，你的鼻孔

720
01:05:15,912 --> 01:05:17,574
<i>it was gritty between your teeth.</i>
你的牙缝里都会有沙尘

721
01:05:18,832 --> 01:05:22,997
<i>Once those dust storms started, they seemed to go on forever.</i>
这些沙尘暴一旦开始就好像再也不会停下一样

722
01:05:25,213 --> 01:05:27,079
No, no, please, I wouldn't like to disturb you.
不，不，请别关，我不想打扰到你

723
01:05:27,173 --> 01:05:28,414
Oh, that's all right.
哦，没关系的

724
01:05:28,716 --> 01:05:30,002
Have you had a letter?
你收到了一封信？

725
01:05:30,427 --> 01:05:32,168
Yes, I had this letter from Mother.
是的，我妈妈的来信

726
01:05:32,804 --> 01:05:34,295
They got as far as Palghat.
他们已经到了巴尔卡德了

727
01:05:34,347 --> 01:05:37,055
- Oh, that's a good, isn't it?
他们还挺快的
- They send you greetings.
他们向你问好

728
01:05:37,392 --> 01:05:38,599
See it says...
看，上面写着

729
01:05:38,643 --> 01:05:41,431
<i>Hot winds whistled and columns of dust</i>
热风呼啸，沙漠里的沙尘

730
01:05:41,521 --> 01:05:43,638
<i>came blowing in from the desert.</i>
不断来袭

731
01:05:44,941 --> 01:05:46,978
No wonder everyone went mad.
毫无疑问，所有人都失去了理智

732
01:05:47,902 --> 01:05:48,902
I gave up.
我放弃了

733
01:05:50,029 --> 01:05:54,239
I simply lay in bed, too lethargic to do a thing.
只好躺在床上，提不起精神做任何事

734
01:05:54,701 --> 01:05:56,943
And I was a young man then, mind you.
请注意，当时我还是个年轻人

735
01:06:05,170 --> 01:06:07,833
But then it was decided we were to go to the mountains,
但后来我们决定去爬山

736
01:06:07,922 --> 01:06:10,665
into the cool air, not to Simla,
去一个凉爽的地方，但不是西米拉

737
01:06:10,967 --> 01:06:15,883
where all the official British types went, but to Masuri, where the Nawab had a house.
一个英国官员都去的地方。是马苏里，土邦王在那儿有一套房子

738
01:06:17,974 --> 01:06:21,558
Well, we all packed up and there was great excitement
我们都准备好行李，非常地兴奋

739
01:06:21,603 --> 01:06:25,643
and relief and I can tell you we could hardly wait to get up there.
有种解放了的感觉，我可以告诉你，我们迫不及待想去那里

740
01:06:26,858 --> 01:06:30,477
Then the begum heard an owl.
可是女王听见猫头鹰叫

741
01:06:31,154 --> 01:06:33,362
Or at least I think it was an owl.
反正我觉得是猫头鹰

742
01:06:33,865 --> 01:06:36,858
Anyway, it was something inauspicious,
无所谓了，这是不详的征兆

743
01:06:37,035 --> 01:06:40,324
a warning that we must on no accounts set out on a journey.
警告我们决不能踏上这场旅途

744
01:07:08,983 --> 01:07:12,021
The Nawab was very restless, excited,
土邦王当时非常焦躁，兴奋

745
01:07:12,904 --> 01:07:14,520
never sat still for a minute.
坐立不安

746
01:07:15,448 --> 01:07:18,156
He was very short tempered with all of us.
还经常对我们发脾气

747
01:07:19,494 --> 01:07:21,952
I couldn't help remembering what I'd heard,
我突然想起来我听到的

748
01:07:22,163 --> 01:07:26,624
about how he was in league with Tikaram's gang.
他是如何和普兰达那群强盗结盟的

749
01:07:28,336 --> 01:07:30,794
Tikaram was a dacoit
普兰达是一个强盗

750
01:07:30,880 --> 01:07:35,625
with a price of 10,000 rupees on his head.
他的头颅价值一万卢比

751
01:07:36,219 --> 01:07:38,506
He and his gang went all around the countryside
他和他的团伙在乡下四处抢劫
752
01:07:38,555 --> 01:07:42,720
looting people and killing anyone who got in their way,
并杀害阻止他们的人

753
01:07:42,809 --> 01:07:44,892
or even just for the fun of it.
甚至只是为了好玩儿

754
01:07:46,271 --> 01:07:48,058
They could do all this with impunity
他们的所作所为不收制约

755
01:07:48,314 --> 01:07:50,977
because they enjoyed the Nawab's protection.
因为他们享有土邦王的保护特权

756
01:07:51,651 --> 01:07:53,734
At least, that's what the British said.
至少英国方面是这么说的

757
01:07:54,320 --> 01:08:00,317
They said he took a share in their loot and used them as his henchmen
他们说土邦王和强盗们分享战利品，并把他们当成自己的亲信

758
01:08:01,119 --> 01:08:02,735
and if anyone informed on them
如果有人举报他们

759
01:08:03,037 --> 01:08:05,745
they would take their revenge on a whole village.
他们会报复整个村庄

760
01:08:55,882 --> 01:08:57,748
If something really horrible happened...
如果非常严重的事情发生了

761
01:08:59,677 --> 01:09:02,545
don't you think I ought to... help you bear it?
你觉得我不应该帮你分担吗？

762
01:09:08,561 --> 01:09:10,097
It all started in a...
这一切发生在

763
01:09:11,856 --> 01:09:13,893
in a house in Chota bazaar.
卓塔集市的一间屋子里

764
01:09:13,941 --> 01:09:16,979
Two women quarrelling over a bucket of water.
两个女人因为一桶水吵了起来

765
01:09:18,738 --> 01:09:24,609
But in this season, with the heat coming on, things grow and build up
但在这个季节，炎热的天气就要来了，万物复苏，繁荣生长

766
01:09:24,702 --> 01:09:27,139
and before you know where you are, you have a full scale riot on your hands
当你意识到你身处何地时，你接手了一场大规模的骚乱

767
01:09:27,163 --> 01:09:28,870
and then there's no holding anyone.
却没抓到任何人

768
01:09:31,626 --> 01:09:35,165
They were throwing acid today.
今天他们互相泼酸

769
01:09:39,801 --> 01:09:41,588
They were aiming for the face, eyes.
泼向对方的脸，眼睛

770
01:09:44,597 --> 01:09:45,597
The screams.
那些惨叫声

771
01:09:48,101 --> 01:09:49,888
I'll never forget those screams.
我永远都忘不了那些惨叫声

772
01:10:43,740 --> 01:10:46,448
- Superintendent, one round only.
指挥官，只来一轮
- Take aim.
瞄准

773
01:10:48,244 --> 01:10:50,406
Fire.
开火

774
01:10:52,206 --> 01:10:54,351
The British also suspected the Nawab
英国人还怀疑土邦王

775
01:10:54,375 --> 01:10:58,540
of using the dacoits to help inflame riots against them
利用盗贼的势力帮助暴徒反抗他们

776
01:10:59,297 --> 01:11:02,415
like the one outside the Satipur Jail in,
比如赛提普监狱外的那场暴乱

777
01:11:03,384 --> 01:11:04,670
I think it was 1923.
我记得是1923年

778
01:11:05,470 --> 01:11:10,306
Anyway, Crawford was away on tour and Douglas was in charge
不管怎样，克劳福德出去游玩了，道格拉斯主事

779
01:11:10,558 --> 01:11:14,848
and had to arrest the ringleaders of what had been a very ugly massacre.
而且不得不抓捕导致这场血流成河的大屠杀的暴徒首领

780
01:11:18,232 --> 01:11:21,646
Well, when all these kinds of things happened
当这一切发生的时候

781
01:11:21,944 --> 01:11:24,937
I just gave up and ran away to Olivia's house
我只好放弃，逃到奥莉维亚的家里

782
01:11:25,156 --> 01:11:26,943
and begged her to play some Schumann.
请她弹奏一些舒曼的曲子

783
01:11:41,422 --> 01:11:42,538
Lovely.
好听

784
01:11:44,801 --> 01:11:45,801
Lovely.
真好听

785
01:12:25,550 --> 01:12:28,418
You don't mind if Harry stays with us for a day or two, do you?
你不介意哈里在我们家住一两天吧？

786
01:12:28,678 --> 01:12:29,678
What?
什么？

787
01:12:30,972 --> 01:12:31,972
Oh, no.
哦，不介意

788
01:12:33,516 --> 01:12:35,303
No, no, I want him to.
我希望他留在这儿

789
01:12:36,894 --> 01:12:38,886
It's better for him to be here than there.
他在这儿总比皇宫好

790
01:13:08,801 --> 01:13:10,292
<i>Bra vissima.</i>
太棒了

791
01:13:10,720 --> 01:13:11,927
Oh, what fun.
真有意思

792
01:13:12,263 --> 01:13:14,380
You do know Mr Hamilton-Paul, don't you, Beth?
贝丝，你认识汉密尔顿先生，对吧？

793
01:13:14,682 --> 01:13:17,800
I most certainly do, we've met oh so many times at the palace.
当然认识了，我们在皇宫的时候碰到过很多次

794
01:13:17,894 --> 01:13:19,635
He's come to stay with us for a while.
他来我们家住一段时间

795
01:13:19,770 --> 01:13:22,103
Oh, I'm so glad that you're not alone at this time.
我非常开心，你现在不会感到孤单了

796
01:13:22,231 --> 01:13:24,598
Not that there's anything whatsoever to worry about Olivia.
奥莉维亚，你也没什么可担心的了

797
01:13:24,650 --> 01:13:26,450
That's what I came here to speak to you about.
这也是我要和你说的

798
01:13:26,944 --> 01:13:30,813
And Arthur is back and he and Douglas have the situation absolutely in hand.
亚瑟回来了，他和道格拉斯完全展控了现在的形式

799
01:13:31,449 --> 01:13:34,942
- What situation?
什么形势？
- Oh you know, the usual.
你知道的，和平常一样

800
01:13:35,036 --> 01:13:36,036
You mustn't think about.
你别多想

801
01:13:36,078 --> 01:13:38,078
Now what I really want you to think about is Simla.
现在我希望你认真考虑的是西米拉

802
01:13:38,748 --> 01:13:43,288
No dear I'm not nagging at you, but we really all do feel...
亲爱的，我没有，没有唠叨你，但我们都觉得

803
01:13:43,336 --> 01:13:46,545
It's true Olivia, you shouldn't be here through the summer, it's unbearable.
奥莉维亚，你真的不该整个夏天都待在这里，这里酷热不堪

804
01:13:46,589 --> 01:13:49,127
- But if you can bear it?
但既然你能忍受？
- Who said I could?
谁说我可以了？

805
01:13:51,177 --> 01:13:53,965
One summer we did manage to get up to Masuri.
有一个夏天，我们的确去了马苏里避暑

806
01:13:54,096 --> 01:13:55,883
The Nawab has a marvellous house up there,
土邦王有一所非常豪华的房子在那儿

807
01:13:55,932 --> 01:13:59,175
it's a swish chalet with a dash of gothic cathedral.
瑞士小木屋，还有哥特式的教堂

808
01:13:59,226 --> 01:14:00,512
Very impressive indeed.
让人印象非常深刻

809
01:14:00,895 --> 01:14:02,761
Not that I got much time to enjoy it.
可我当时没有太多的时间享受

810
01:14:02,897 --> 01:14:06,641
A dead bat was found in all of places the begum's bedroom
因为女王的卧室里发现了一只死蝙蝠

811
01:14:06,817 --> 01:14:09,025
so we had to pack up and come back home immediately.
所以我们不得不立刻收拾行李回家

812
01:14:09,987 --> 01:14:11,715
Actually, this year I wasn't thinking so much
实际上，今年我想回家

813
01:14:11,739 --> 01:14:14,026
of going to the mountains as of going home.
并没有考虑去山里避暑

814
01:14:14,784 --> 01:14:16,696
You see I'm worried about my mother,
你懂的，我母亲最近身体不太好

815
01:14:17,119 --> 01:14:18,701
she hasn't been too well and...
我很担心她

816
01:14:18,955 --> 01:14:20,662
Well, of course you must go.
那你当然要回去了

817
01:14:21,457 --> 01:14:22,914
And do you know the Ross-Milbanks?
你认识罗斯・米尔班克吗？

818
01:14:23,250 --> 01:14:25,993
He's been the DC over at Cawnpore.
他一直是坎普尔的首脑

819
01:14:26,629 --> 01:14:29,121
They're on home leave now driving down to Bombay
他们要休假回家，正开车去孟买

820
01:14:29,173 --> 01:14:30,414
to catch the P&O
赶P&O火车

821
01:14:30,466 --> 01:14:33,425
But those P&O aren't they always booked up,
但P&O的车票经常订满

822
01:14:33,636 --> 01:14:35,298
completely booked, months ahead?
不是要提前几个月预定吗？

823
01:14:35,429 --> 01:14:37,341
Oh, but a single berth.
哦，但只是一张单人票而已

824
01:14:37,723 --> 01:14:40,557
And we could always send a cable to the Gibbons in Bombay.
我们总是可以给孟买的吉本斯发电报

825
01:14:40,977 --> 01:14:43,469
- Really?
真的吗？
- Really and truly.
真的，千真万确

826
01:14:45,731 --> 01:14:48,223
Mr Gandhi's lot probably stirring things up again.
甘地先生可能又在挑起事端了

827
01:14:48,317 --> 01:14:49,774
They never miss a chance.
他们不放过任何一次机会

828
01:14:59,578 --> 01:15:01,160
No, don't bother to get up.
不用了，别劳神起身了

829
01:15:02,832 --> 01:15:04,368
Where are Mr and Mrs Rivers?
里佛斯夫妇在哪儿？

830
01:15:04,875 --> 01:15:07,492
They've gone to church and then I think they're going to the club.
他们去教堂了，接着我想他们会去俱乐部

831
01:15:09,171 --> 01:15:10,537
Oh, what's here?
这都是什么？

832
01:15:12,508 --> 01:15:16,127
Tea, toast and marmalade, boiled eggs three minutes,
茶，烤面包，果酱，煮了三分钟的鸡蛋

833
01:15:16,637 --> 01:15:18,128
an English newspaper.
一份英国报纸

834
01:15:18,681 --> 01:15:20,889
Four months old but yes it's English.
四个月前的了，不过确实是英国报纸

835
01:15:23,769 --> 01:15:26,352
Well, I can see you have thoroughly deserted us.
在我看来，你是已经彻底抛弃我们了

836
01:15:27,898 --> 01:15:30,356
My poor mother and all the ladies keep asking,
我可怜的母亲，还有王妃们不停地问我

837
01:15:30,735 --> 01:15:33,569
"Where is Harry, when is he coming home?"
哈里去哪儿了？什么时候回家？

838
01:15:34,155 --> 01:15:37,739
I answer he <i>is</i> home, he's with his own people whom he loves.
我回答他们，他在家里呢，和他喜欢的人一起生活

839
01:15:39,035 --> 01:15:40,321
Isn't that true?
我说的不对吗？

840
01:15:41,078 --> 01:15:42,514
Now you see, you don't say anything.
看看，现在你又一言不发

841
01:15:42,538 --> 01:15:44,325
You don't give one a chance to say anything.
是你不给我说话的机会

842
01:15:48,586 --> 01:15:50,828
I know I'm a monster egoist,
我知道我是一个以自我为中心的魔鬼

843
01:15:51,839 --> 01:15:53,501
or a plain monster.
或者纯粹是个魔鬼

844
01:15:55,885 --> 01:15:57,592
But my goodness for a monster,
但作为魔鬼，我也有慈悲之心

845
01:15:57,887 --> 01:15:59,799
I do grow fond of other people
我会渐渐地喜欢上别人

846
01:16:00,598 --> 01:16:01,918
and miss them when they leave me.
当他们离开的时候，还会想念他们

847
01:16:03,559 --> 01:16:04,970
Now what's the matter?
你又怎么了？

848
01:16:05,352 --> 01:16:09,016
- I can just see you missing me.
我只是知道了你想我
- Oh no, of course not.
不，不，当然不是了

849
01:16:09,398 --> 01:16:11,685
I'm here for the sole purpose of leaving my calling card
我来这儿只有一个目的，把我的召见卡

850
01:16:11,776 --> 01:16:13,062
on Mr and Mrs Rivers.
给里弗斯夫妇

851
01:16:17,364 --> 01:16:19,196
Don't be a fool, Harry.
别犯傻了，哈里

852
01:16:20,659 --> 01:16:22,525
You know why I'm here.
你知道我来这里的原因

853
01:16:29,126 --> 01:16:30,958
- See you later, old man.
稍后见，老兄
- Bravo.
稍后见

854
01:16:31,962 --> 01:16:33,999
Oh, Olivia, do tell Mr Hamilton-Paul
奥莉维亚，请转告汉密尔顿保罗

855
01:16:34,048 --> 01:16:36,040
that the Milbanks are getting here on Tuesday
米尔班克周二到

856
01:16:36,133 --> 01:16:37,486
and could take him with them to Bombay.
可以带他一起去孟买

857
01:16:37,510 --> 01:16:39,718
- We have a berth for him.
我们给他买了一张车票
- Good work, Beth.
贝丝，太好了

858
01:16:41,514 --> 01:16:44,973
But darling, Harry's the Nawab's guest.
可是，亲爱的，哈里是土邦王的客人

859
01:16:45,351 --> 01:16:48,469
He can't just run out on him at a moment's notice with Mrs Crawford...
他不能因为克劳德福太太的一句话就抛弃他

860
01:16:48,562 --> 01:16:49,723
- Morning.
早上好
- Morning.
早上好

861
01:16:49,980 --> 01:16:52,848
- ...Mrs Crawford's friends.
还是克劳福德太太的朋友
- I can't see what's wrong with that.
我不觉得有什么问题

862
01:16:55,152 --> 01:16:56,859
But the Nawab paid his fare
但是土邦王支付了他的车费

863
01:16:57,738 --> 01:17:01,197
and he's been keeping him, hasn't he, in the lap of luxury for some time?
这段时间一直让他养尊处优，不是吗？

864
01:17:01,325 --> 01:17:03,362
He shouldn't be there in the first place.
他一开始就不应该住在那里

865
01:17:08,541 --> 01:17:11,204
No Englishman has any business living in that palace.
英国人不该和那座皇室扯上关系

866
01:17:11,752 --> 01:17:13,084
Don't be so stuffy.
别这么古板

867
01:17:15,297 --> 01:17:16,297
I'm sorry.
对不起

868
01:17:17,133 --> 01:17:20,467
Those are my feelings and I must be allowed to express them.
这都是我的感受，我有权表达出来

869
01:17:25,099 --> 01:17:27,637
I could do without this particular Sunday caller.
要是没有这个特别的周日召见就好了

870
01:17:34,942 --> 01:17:36,478
I'm delighted to see you.
很高兴见到你

871
01:17:36,735 --> 01:17:38,897
Mrs Rivers, what a charming dress.
里弗斯太太，你的裙子真漂亮

872
01:17:39,238 --> 01:17:42,447
And Mr Rivers, I'm more than delighted to congratulate you on your handling
里弗斯先生，我无比荣幸地恭喜你解决了

873
01:17:42,491 --> 01:17:45,154
the Chota bazaar incident. You were most prompt.
卓塔集市的袭击  你是最果断的

874
01:17:45,703 --> 01:17:47,139
I wish I'd been prompt enough to get there
我希望我的果断是在袭击发生之前

875
01:17:47,163 --> 01:17:48,779
before rather than after the event.
而不是袭击之后

876
01:17:48,914 --> 01:17:51,156
Oh, Mr Rivers, what can be done?
哦，里弗斯先生，还能做些什么呢？

877
01:17:51,208 --> 01:17:52,574
These people will never learn.
民众从来不吸取教训

878
01:17:52,668 --> 01:17:56,082
As to your conduct in this miserable affair there's nothing but praise.
至于你在这次暴乱中的表现，让人十分钦佩

879
01:17:56,589 --> 01:17:57,921
You are misinformed.
您理解错了

880
01:17:58,465 --> 01:18:00,172
It sparked off a lot of resentment.
这次暴乱产生了很多怨恨

881
01:18:00,843 --> 01:18:03,683
You must've heard of all the troubles outside the jail and other places.
您一定听说了，监狱和其他宫廷外的冲突

882
01:18:04,221 --> 01:18:06,338
They get hot and then they cool off.
他们一会儿发起暴乱，过会儿就停止了

883
01:18:06,432 --> 01:18:07,968
It's like our weather and its season.
就像这里的季节和天气一样

884
01:18:08,350 --> 01:18:09,886
Please get dressed, we must go.
请换好衣服，我们该走了

885
01:18:10,019 --> 01:18:12,386
Oh, Mrs Crawford asked us to tell you that the Milbanks
对了，克劳福德太太要我们转告你，米尔班克

886
01:18:12,438 --> 01:18:15,181
are arriving on Tuesday and they're expecting you to go with them.
周二就到了，希望你和他们一起走

887
01:18:15,274 --> 01:18:17,891
Oh, to Bombay?  Yes, Harry told me about it.
去孟买吗？是的，哈里和我说了

888
01:18:18,527 --> 01:18:20,189
Please get dressed, my dear fellow.
我亲爱的朋友，请换好衣服

889
01:18:20,237 --> 01:18:22,604
I hope you don't expect me to take you home in this state.
你不希望我把这个装扮的你带回家吧？

890
01:18:22,656 --> 01:18:25,945
Mrs Crawford says that they have booked a berth for you.
克劳福德太太还说，他们给你订了一张车票

891
01:18:26,035 --> 01:18:30,120
There's been a misunderstanding. I shall apologise to Mrs Crawford myself
这其中一定是有误会，我会亲自向克劳德福太太致歉的

892
01:18:30,206 --> 01:18:32,869
and thank her for her kind efforts on behalf of my guest.
并谢谢她对我的客人友好的帮助

893
01:18:33,125 --> 01:18:36,084
But you wanted to go, your mother is ill.
可是你想回去，你妈妈病了

894
01:18:36,670 --> 01:18:37,877
We must be thankful.
我们十分欣慰

895
01:18:38,339 --> 01:18:39,750
Mother is better.
妈妈有所好转了

896
01:18:41,050 --> 01:18:43,963
And my mother has written to her to invite her to the palace.
我妈妈已经写信给她，邀请她来王宫

897
01:18:44,511 --> 01:18:47,299
She has written, I translate from Urdu,
她已经写完了，我做的翻译

898
01:18:47,723 --> 01:18:50,306
"You now have not one son but two..."
您现在不是有一个儿子，而是两个

899
01:18:50,559 --> 01:18:52,846
"...and both your sons are eager for your visit."
而您的两个儿子都期待您的到来

900
01:18:53,646 --> 01:18:55,888
Thanks awfully for having me.
非常感谢你们收留我

901
01:18:58,108 --> 01:19:01,067
It's true, you know, I do want to go back to the palace.
你知道的，我是真的想回到皇宫去

902
01:19:01,904 --> 01:19:03,645
We talked it over before you came.
你们回来之前我们就说过了

903
01:19:04,782 --> 01:19:05,782
I do want to.
我确实想回去

904
01:19:06,283 --> 01:19:07,649
You don't have to.
你可以不回去的

905
01:19:09,161 --> 01:19:10,447
I want to.
可我想回去

906
01:19:10,496 --> 01:19:13,330
Please get dressed, come on.
赶紧去换衣服吧，快去吧

907
01:19:13,874 --> 01:19:16,833
Look at you, is this the way to appear in front of a lady?
看看你自己，要这个样子出现在一位女士面前吗？

908
01:19:23,842 --> 01:19:25,583
You know, he doesn't know what he wants.
你知道，他并不清楚自己想要什么

909
01:19:25,844 --> 01:19:28,052
One day it's this, one day it's that.
今天这样，明天那样

910
01:19:29,223 --> 01:19:30,223
What can I do?
我能怎么办呢？

911
01:19:30,849 --> 01:19:33,842
I've grown fond of him, he's my friend.
他是我的朋友，我越来越喜欢他了

912
01:19:34,728 --> 01:19:38,563
And once I love a friend it's for life, forever.
而且一旦我喜欢一个朋友，都是我一辈子的朋友

913
01:19:39,441 --> 01:19:41,023
Whatever faults he may have.
不管他犯了什么错

914
01:21:00,731 --> 01:21:04,441
I'd love to read some Trollope or Dickens.
我喜欢特罗洛普或狄更斯的书

915
01:21:05,194 --> 01:21:08,938
Lot's of cold, damp, foggy London scenes,
很多寒冷潮湿，雾气蒙蒙的伦敦景色

916
01:21:09,198 --> 01:21:10,860
that's what I'm longing for.
是我一直向往的

917
01:21:11,700 --> 01:21:13,942
Oh, come away, they're all pornographic.
走开，那都是色情小说

918
01:21:20,667 --> 01:21:23,205
It's a princess being got ready for her nuptial night.
一位公主为她的新婚夜做好了准备
919
01:21:23,921 --> 01:21:25,523
They're doing all sorts of intimate things to her.
他们对她做了各种亲密的事情

920
01:21:25,547 --> 01:21:26,547
Come away.
别看了

921
01:21:33,305 --> 01:21:34,967
Harry, what is all this about dacoits?
哈里，这些强盗究竟是怎么回事？

922
01:21:35,516 --> 01:21:37,883
Honestly I don't know, Olivia.
奥莉维亚，说实话，我也不知道

923
01:21:38,894 --> 01:21:42,683
A lot of things go on and, quite frankly, I'd just as soon not know about them.
发生了很多事，老实讲，我可能很快就不记得了

924
01:21:44,441 --> 01:21:45,898
Gosh I feel I awful.
天啊，我感觉糟透了

925
01:21:46,485 --> 01:21:48,852
But Harry, doesn't he ever talk to you about...
可是哈里，他从来没和你讲过……

926
01:21:50,823 --> 01:21:54,988
I hope I'm not disturbing, please say if I am and I'll run away at once.
希望我没有打扰到你们，如果有的话，请告诉我，我马上离开

927
01:21:55,202 --> 01:21:57,785
How very kind of you to come and see our poor patient.
你真的太善良了，来探望我们可怜的病人

928
01:21:58,330 --> 01:22:00,572
How do you find him? I've sent for Dr Puri.
你是怎么找到他的？我已经派人去接普伦医生了

929
01:22:00,666 --> 01:22:03,329
He's a witch doctor, please don't bring him near me.
他是个巫医，请不要让他靠近我

930
01:22:03,377 --> 01:22:04,618
Don't be ridiculous.
别耍性子了

931
01:22:04,920 --> 01:22:07,003
We want you to get well again quickly.
我们希望你迅速的好起来

932
01:22:07,172 --> 01:22:10,506
We miss you. It's very boring without you, isn't it, Olivia?
我们都想你，没有你太无聊了，对吗，奥莉维亚？

933
01:22:10,843 --> 01:22:12,523
She's been asking about the dacoits.
她一直在问强盗的事情

934
01:22:20,352 --> 01:22:22,218
I hope if there's something you want to know
我希望，你如果想知道什么事情的话

935
01:22:22,855 --> 01:22:23,971
you'll ask me,
直接问我，除了我以外

936
01:22:24,815 --> 01:22:27,774
not Harry or anybody else, but me.
不要问哈里或者其他人

937
01:22:29,736 --> 01:22:30,852
What have you heard?
你听说了什么？

938
01:22:31,864 --> 01:22:32,864
What are they saying?
他们是怎么说的？

939
01:22:34,950 --> 01:22:36,407
You must tell me,
你一定要告诉我

940
01:22:36,618 --> 01:22:39,361
you must give me a chance to defend myself against these slanders.
你必须给我一个为自己辩解的机会

941
01:22:39,663 --> 01:22:41,450
What on Earth are you asking her to do?
你到底让她做什么了？

942
01:22:41,957 --> 01:22:44,495
Bring you reports from the Civil Lines at Satipur?
帮你偷赛提普白城的报告吗？

943
01:22:45,127 --> 01:22:46,709
Do you want her to be your spy?
你让她当你的间谍吗？

944
01:22:47,045 --> 01:22:50,459
- I hope you don't think that of me.
我希望你不是这么看我的
- Of course I don't.
我当然没有

945
01:22:51,008 --> 01:22:52,544
I wouldn't for a minute.
一刻也没有

946
01:22:53,844 --> 01:22:54,880
How could you think it?
你怎么能这么想呢？

947
01:22:55,387 --> 01:22:56,719
No, no, I don't.
不，不，我没有

948
01:22:57,890 --> 01:22:59,552
I know you understand me.
我知道你理解我

949
01:23:00,350 --> 01:23:01,557
That's why I trust you.
这也是我相信你的原因

950
01:23:28,045 --> 01:23:31,538
- What did they want?
他们想要什么？
- Protection.
保护

951
01:23:33,133 --> 01:23:35,671
It seems that the same gang who raided that village
好像袭击那个村庄的那群强盗

952
01:23:36,053 --> 01:23:38,420
are now threatening the local traders.
现在在威胁当地的商人

953
01:23:39,973 --> 01:23:43,137
Trying to extort money for themselves and their chief.
为他们自己和首领敲诈更多的钱财

954
01:23:45,062 --> 01:23:46,394
Who's their chief?
他们的首领是谁？

955
01:23:47,773 --> 01:23:51,141
Well, we suspect our friend.
我们怀疑是我们的朋友

956
01:23:52,653 --> 01:23:54,110
Do you mean the Nawab?
你是说土邦王吗？

957
01:23:55,197 --> 01:23:58,440
But he's a ruler, he wouldn't get mixed up with a robber gang.
他是个统治者，才不会和一群盗贼同流合污呢

958
01:23:58,867 --> 01:24:00,233
After all, he's a prince.
毕竟，他是个王子

959
01:24:00,285 --> 01:24:02,368
Yes, and he's bankrupt,
是的，加上他破产了

960
01:24:03,038 --> 01:24:05,030
having bled his unfortunate subject's wife
他那个不幸的第一任妻子或多或少地
961
01:24:05,082 --> 01:24:07,995
by means of more or less legitimate extortion.
通过法律手段瓜分了他的财产

962
01:24:09,044 --> 01:24:11,127
He's now taken to cruder methods.
虽然听起来很不舒服

963
01:24:12,422 --> 01:24:15,415
Not to put too fine a point on it to outright robbery.
但他已经采取粗暴的方式直接抢劫

964
01:24:15,926 --> 01:24:17,838
I don't believe a word of it.
我一点儿也不相信

965
01:24:20,597 --> 01:24:22,429
Must you smoke that dashed thing...
这么热的天，你一定要抽

966
01:24:25,310 --> 01:24:26,391
in this heat?
那个破玩儿意吗？

967
01:24:29,439 --> 01:24:30,646
You should've gone to Simla.
你应该去西米拉的

968
01:24:30,941 --> 01:24:35,561
And do what, go for walks with Beth Crawford?
去做什么？和贝丝・克劳福德一起散步吗？

969
01:24:36,863 --> 01:24:39,947
Go to the same old boring old dinner parties.
反复参加那些古板无聊的晚宴吗？

970
01:24:40,659 --> 01:24:43,197
One more of those and I shall lie down and die.
你再提一次，我就躺下等死

971
01:24:47,207 --> 01:24:49,073
I don't know what's the matter with me.
我不知道我是怎么了

972
01:24:50,460 --> 01:24:54,329
Why I get so worked up over every little thing.
为什么总是因为一点儿小事就发脾气呢？

973
01:24:55,090 --> 01:24:58,083
I told you, it's the heat.
我告诉你了，是天气热的原因

974
01:24:59,469 --> 01:25:02,052
No Englishwoman is supposed to stand this weather.
没有一个英国女人可以忍受这种炎热的天气

975
01:25:03,223 --> 01:25:05,055
You have these set notions
你已经给英国女人

976
01:25:05,100 --> 01:25:08,468
about what English women are supposed to stand.
能忍受什么设立了标准

977
01:25:09,646 --> 01:25:11,353
Why should anyone tell me what I can stand
为什么每个人都告诉我，我能忍受什么

978
01:25:11,398 --> 01:25:12,730
and what I can't stand?
我不能忍受什么呢？

979
01:25:15,944 --> 01:25:17,310
If you really want to know
如果你真的想知道

980
01:25:17,654 --> 01:25:20,488
the one thing I can't stand is English women.
我不能忍受的一件事，那就是英国女人

981
01:25:21,450 --> 01:25:23,032
Memsahibs.
小姐们

982
01:25:25,329 --> 01:25:26,570
But the rest...
至于其他的

983
01:25:30,250 --> 01:25:33,869
I'm so happy here, I never want to go away.
我在这儿非常开心，从没想过要离开

984
01:25:45,098 --> 01:25:47,511
I wish you would tell Dr Saunders to go and see Harry
我希望你让桑德斯医生去看看哈里

985
01:25:47,601 --> 01:25:50,435
at the palace, he just isn't getting any better.
在王宫里，他一点儿都没有好转

986
01:25:51,563 --> 01:25:52,770
Well...
好的

987
01:25:54,399 --> 01:25:56,641
Dr Saunders doesn't really see private patients
桑德斯医生不怎么看私人病人

988
01:25:56,735 --> 01:25:58,271
unless it's one of us.
除非是我们中的一个

989
01:25:59,780 --> 01:26:01,442
Isn't in Harry one of us？
哈里不是我们中的一员吗？

990
01:26:02,574 --> 01:26:06,909
And if not, am I one of us, do you think?
假如他不是，你认为我是吗？

991
01:26:15,337 --> 01:26:18,455
It might even be that I love you because you're not.
也许正因为你不是，我才爱你

992
01:26:21,009 --> 01:26:23,626
You know sometimes I wish I could afford some feelings,
你知道，有时候我希望自己能释放一些情绪

993
01:26:24,846 --> 01:26:27,884
because I get hot too, I get angry, I want to lose my temper, but...
因为我也热，我也愤怒，我也想发脾气，但是


994
01:26:30,560 --> 01:26:34,099
there are always people watching everywhere.
到处都有人在监视

995
01:26:36,191 --> 01:26:39,480
One simply cannot.
我就是不能

996
01:26:40,696 --> 01:26:42,028
Not even for a minute.
甚至一分钟也不能

997
01:26:45,909 --> 01:26:47,445
It's a bore I know.
我知道这很无聊

998
01:26:51,915 --> 01:26:54,498
When we have a baby, I want him to be just like you.
等我们有了孩子，我要他像你一样

999
01:26:54,960 --> 01:26:57,623
No, no, like you.
不，不，要像你

1000
01:26:58,922 --> 01:26:59,922
Like Olivia.
像奥莉维亚

1001
01:27:01,091 --> 01:27:02,923
Oh, Olivia's no good.
哦，奥莉维亚不好

1002
01:27:03,844 --> 01:27:05,506
Oh, don't say that.
哦，别这么说

1003
01:27:15,814 --> 01:27:18,602
Oh, it's all out of tune.
哦，全都不在调上

1004
01:27:19,234 --> 01:27:20,520
There's no one to play it.
这里没人会弹钢琴

1005
01:27:21,361 --> 01:27:22,977
I'd ordered it for my wife.
这是我为我妻子定制的

1006
01:27:23,447 --> 01:27:25,860
- Did she play?
她弹过吗？
- She was keen to learn...
她认真的学习过

1007
01:27:27,242 --> 01:27:29,484
but by the time the piano arrived, she had left.
可是这架钢琴送到的时候，她已经离开了

1008
01:27:32,164 --> 01:27:34,622
I suppose you know about my marriage?
我猜你已经知道我的婚姻状况了？

1009
01:27:34,958 --> 01:27:36,199
I've heard.
我听说过

1010
01:27:36,668 --> 01:27:38,955
Oh yes, of course you must've heard a lot of things.
当然了，你一定听说了很多事

1011
01:27:39,796 --> 01:27:41,913
There are always people to spread lies about me,
人们总是到处散播我的谣言

1012
01:27:42,382 --> 01:27:44,214
including my wife's family.
包括我妻子的娘家
 
1013
01:27:48,138 --> 01:27:50,130
She was much too young for me, Olivia.
她比我小太多了，奥莉维亚

1014
01:27:52,017 --> 01:27:54,930
I loved her, as one loves a child.
我爱她就像爱一个孩子一样

1015
01:27:56,021 --> 01:27:58,354
Not as I would love a woman.
不是爱一个女人

1016
01:28:10,452 --> 01:28:11,613
What a pity.
真可惜

1017
01:29:22,899 --> 01:29:24,502
You know, I know what happened, more or less.
你知道的，我或多或少意识到有什么事发生了

1018
01:29:24,526 --> 01:29:27,735
After all, it's quite easy to find out
what a person did, but...
毕竟，很容易就能发现一个人做了什么，但是

1019
01:29:28,780 --> 01:29:29,941
what made them do it.
什么促使他们那样做了呢

1020
01:29:46,506 --> 01:29:47,872
I don't know.
我不知道

1021
01:29:48,091 --> 01:29:52,802
I was thinking how India changes people.
我在想印度是如何改变人们的

1022
01:29:55,265 --> 01:29:57,473
Just in subtle ways.
潜移默化中就改变了

1023
01:29:59,019 --> 01:30:00,601
Just by being here.
站在这里就足够了

1024
01:30:01,855 --> 01:30:04,017
I feel you have changed.
我觉得你变了

1025
01:30:05,609 --> 01:30:09,774
But you're still too much in your head, not in your heart.
可你脑袋里还是装了太多东西，心里却没与

1026
01:30:10,864 --> 01:30:12,321
I suppose so.
也许是吧

1027
01:30:12,949 --> 01:30:14,656
Oh, but I admire you.
但我很欣赏你

1028
01:30:14,910 --> 01:30:16,276
You're so...
你太

1029
01:30:17,746 --> 01:30:19,203
philosophical.
 你太理智了

1030
01:30:21,708 --> 01:30:23,324
I don't want to be philosophical.
我不想变得理智

1031
01:30:23,835 --> 01:30:25,747
Oh, what do you want to be then?
那你想变成什么样？

1032
01:30:26,546 --> 01:30:29,755
I don't know, like other people.
不知道，和其他人一样吧

1033
01:30:33,303 --> 01:30:35,886
You know when you talk like that to me,
你知道吗，当你和我讲那些话的时候

1034
01:30:36,264 --> 01:30:38,847
I don't always unders...
我不总是

1035
01:30:41,561 --> 01:30:44,099
I don't always understand you.
我不总是能理解你

1036
01:30:47,651 --> 01:30:51,315
But when we are together like this,
担当我们像现在这样在一起的时候

1037
01:30:53,365 --> 01:30:55,948
I feel you are my very great friend.
我觉得你是我非常好的朋友

1038
01:30:56,534 --> 01:30:58,867
I am your very great friend.
我就是你非常好的朋友

1039
01:31:22,602 --> 01:31:23,934
Hello.
嗨

1040
01:31:24,187 --> 01:31:25,723
Were you waiting for me?
你是在等我吗？

1041
01:31:29,150 --> 01:31:30,561
I hoped you were.
我希望你在等我

1042
01:32:10,358 --> 01:32:12,044
You must excuse me, Rivers, but these people are enough
里弗斯，你务必原谅我，但这些人

1043
01:32:12,068 --> 01:32:13,900
to drive anyone out of their mind.
谁都忍受不了

1044
01:32:14,571 --> 01:32:16,424
They bring me some woman pretending she's miscarrying
他们带来一些女人，假装流产了

1045
01:32:16,448 --> 01:32:18,690
and when I curette her I discover...
当我用刮匙检查的时候发现

1046
01:32:21,494 --> 01:32:24,783
it's always the same, they've aborted her.
他们给这些女人堕胎的方法一模一样

1047
01:32:25,373 --> 01:32:27,615
They stick this twig into her and do it with that.
把这个树枝插进女人的身体里帮她们堕胎

1048
01:32:28,168 --> 01:32:30,160
Abortion, mind you, it's a criminal act.
我要提醒你，堕胎是违法的

1049
01:32:30,628 --> 01:32:32,335
And then they try to fool me.
他们居然想骗我

1050
01:32:34,382 --> 01:32:37,170
I'm sorry you had to come in on this, Rivers, what can I do for you?
里佛斯，很抱歉让你听我发牢骚，你找我有什么事吗？

1051
01:32:39,429 --> 01:32:42,046
I wanted to ask you a particular favour.
我有个不情之请

1052
01:32:42,432 --> 01:32:44,799
You know Harry Hamilton-Paul who's staying at the palace?
你认识皇宫里那个哈里・汉密尔顿保罗吗？

1053
01:32:44,851 --> 01:32:46,058
Oh yes, yeah, him.
哦，哈里，认识

1054
01:32:46,102 --> 01:32:48,719
He's not very well and Olivia and I thought that it'd...
他身体不太好，我和奥莉维亚想

1055
01:32:48,772 --> 01:32:49,772
Well.
好吧

1056
01:32:50,523 --> 01:32:51,751
I wonder what he's been eating over there.
我想知道他在皇宫里一直吃什么

1057
01:32:59,866 --> 01:33:02,904
You see it's question of diet, Nawab Sahib.
土邦王陛下，这是饮食习惯的问题

1058
01:33:03,078 --> 01:33:05,786
I've seen hundreds of cases like this, thousands.
我见过成百上千个这样的病人

1059
01:33:05,955 --> 01:33:11,201
Did you know that most Indians suffer from amoebic dysentery, it's a fact.
你知道大多数印度人都患有阿米巴痢疾吗？这是事实

1060
01:33:11,252 --> 01:33:14,620
- Is that true? How interesting.
真的吗？那太有意思了
- They try and cheat you.
他们想方设法地骗你

1061
01:33:14,839 --> 01:33:16,171
When I say, "What did you eat?"
当我问，你吃了什么？

1062
01:33:16,257 --> 01:33:18,123
They'll say, "Only what you said Dr Sahib,"
他们回答，萨希卜医生，都是听从您的要求

1063
01:33:18,176 --> 01:33:19,542
but of course they can't fool me.
但事实上，他们骗不了我

1064
01:33:19,761 --> 01:33:22,799
"Oh yes, and what about those chilies, hmm?"
是吗？那这些辣椒是怎么回事？

1065
01:33:23,056 --> 01:33:27,221
"And that curry you've had? What, you liar, you cheat?"
这就是你所谓的咖喱吗？简直是睁眼说瞎话

1066
01:33:28,061 --> 01:33:29,427
Sometimes I don't waste any time.
有时候我不会浪费时间

1067
01:33:29,479 --> 01:33:31,562
I smartly box their ears, one, two, one, two.
直接给他们几个耳光，一二，一二

1068
01:33:31,606 --> 01:33:34,794
- It's the only language they understand.
这是他们唯一能听懂的两个词
- You're absolutely right, Dr Saunders.
桑德斯医生，你说的很对

1069
01:33:34,818 --> 01:33:37,561
Well, it's no use arguing with them. They're not amenable to reason.
跟他们争论也没用，他们不懂得推理

1070
01:33:38,196 --> 01:33:42,361
They haven't got it here you see, up here, the way we have.
他们不会像我们这样用脑，思考问题

1071
01:33:44,410 --> 01:33:46,868
He really is exceptionally obnoxious.
他真的非常招人讨厌

1072
01:33:47,413 --> 01:33:50,281
- Please don't judge us by him.
请不要用他来评判我们
- Who's us?
我们是谁？

1073
01:33:50,667 --> 01:33:53,501
I don't know how you feel about it, but don't lump me in with that lot.
我不知道你是怎么想的，但请不要把我和他们混为一谈

1074
01:33:53,628 --> 01:33:56,917
Harry, you can't say the Crawfords are like Dr Saunders,
哈里，你不会认为克劳福德夫妇像桑德斯医生

1075
01:33:57,048 --> 01:34:00,257
or the Minnies, or for that matter, Douglas.
或明尼夫妇一样吧，又或者是道格拉斯

1076
01:34:00,301 --> 01:34:01,462
And you?
那你呢？

1077
01:34:01,803 --> 01:34:03,385
They're all the same.
他们都是一类人

1078
01:34:03,721 --> 01:34:06,134
So you do lump me in with them.
所以你确实认为我和他们一样

1079
01:34:06,599 --> 01:34:10,218
You, I wouldn't for a minute, not for a minute think of you,
你，我一刻也没有，一刻也没有这么想

1080
01:34:10,270 --> 01:34:11,761
speak of you in the same breath.
同时也没有批判你

1081
01:34:13,106 --> 01:34:17,441
To me, you're better, beautiful, wonderful,
对我来说，你，美丽大方善良

1082
01:34:17,902 --> 01:34:20,895
more wonderful, absolutely terrific.
你是最美丽的，非常完美

1083
01:34:21,656 --> 01:34:25,775
- Is that what you wanted to hear?
这是你想听的吗？
- Harry, Olivia, look, I mean,
哈里，奥莉维亚，你们听我说

1084
01:34:26,411 --> 01:34:29,199
instead of having a rotten time let's have some fun.
与其在这儿虚度时光，不如找点儿乐子

1085
01:34:30,665 --> 01:34:34,579
Let me tell you a dream, my dream, my latest dream, you know.
我和你们讲一个梦，一个我的梦，我最近做的梦，你们知道吗
 
1086
01:34:34,669 --> 01:34:36,786
I dreamt of Mrs Crawford.
我梦见了克劳福德太太

1087
01:34:37,881 --> 01:34:41,215
- You dream about Mrs Crawford?
你梦见了克劳福德太太？
- Not the way you mean, I mean,
不是你想的那样，我的意思是

1088
01:34:41,885 --> 01:34:44,673
Mrs Crawford was not Mrs Crawford.
克劳福德太太，不是克劳福德太太

1089
01:34:45,013 --> 01:34:47,505
- She was a hijra.
她是个宦官
- What's a hijra?
宦官是什么？

1090
01:34:47,557 --> 01:34:49,799
Oh my poor Olivia, you don't know?
哦，我的傻奥莉维亚，你不知道吗？

1091
01:34:50,143 --> 01:34:51,759
We must educate her.
看来我们要教教她

1092
01:35:09,913 --> 01:35:12,030
At first, she couldn't work out
一开始，她不知道

1093
01:35:12,081 --> 01:35:14,118
that these were men, eunuchs.
那些宦官是男人

1094
01:35:14,209 --> 01:35:16,201
- Hijra?
宦官？
- Yes.
是的

1095
01:35:17,253 --> 01:35:20,621
It was all so strange and wonderfully exotic
在充满异国风情的奇妙世界里

1096
01:35:21,216 --> 01:35:24,300
and she forgot everything, joined in the fun.
她抛开一切享受其中的快乐

1097
01:35:24,969 --> 01:35:27,336
Forgot herself, you might say.
可以说达到忘我的境界

1098
01:36:29,284 --> 01:36:32,368
I kept trying to warn her but she wouldn't listen.
我一直试着提醒她，但她不听

1099
01:36:33,454 --> 01:36:36,242
You see, she was outraging two conventions,
你知道的，她违背了双方的约定

1100
01:36:36,499 --> 01:36:39,833
those of her own people and those of the Indians,
一方是她自己的国家，一方的印度

1101
01:36:40,003 --> 01:36:43,622
whose conventions are, if anything, even stronger
如果发生什么事，就看哪一方更强大了

1102
01:36:43,965 --> 01:36:46,548
and of course you can't do anything in India
当然在印度，你的一举一动
1103
01:36:46,592 --> 01:36:48,584
without everyone knowing about it,
家喻户晓

1104
01:36:48,845 --> 01:36:50,381
the servants see to that.
仆人们会看着办的

1105
01:37:07,697 --> 01:37:09,466
You know, there's a story about that old woman
你听过一个老女人

1106
01:37:09,490 --> 01:37:10,856
in the purdah quarters.
在营房的故事吗？

1107
01:37:11,159 --> 01:37:13,071
How she killed off an unwanted bride
她给婚纱染上毒药水

1108
01:37:13,119 --> 01:37:16,283
by dressing her up in poisoned wedding gowns.
毒死了一位不受欢迎的新娘

1109
01:37:16,331 --> 01:37:17,331
What?
什么？

1110
01:37:17,749 --> 01:37:19,115
Apparently it's true.
千真万确

1111
01:37:19,584 --> 01:37:21,075
They dipped the cloth into poison
他们把婚纱浸泡在毒水里

1112
01:37:21,127 --> 01:37:23,835
and then when you put it on it clings to you.
当你穿上婚纱的时候，你就中毒了

1113
01:37:23,963 --> 01:37:25,079
Frightful.
真可怕

1114
01:37:25,131 --> 01:37:28,465
Oh, there are all sorts of stories about what goes on in the purdah quarters.
营房里流传着各种各样的故事

1115
01:37:28,718 --> 01:37:31,301
Secret arts, magic potions and all the rest of it.
邪术，魔法药水，应有尽有

1116
01:37:31,346 --> 01:37:34,555
Oh, come on now, those old things in there?
不会吧，现在还有这种古老的方法？

1117
01:37:36,225 --> 01:37:37,466
Do they know about me?
他们知道我吗？

1118
01:37:40,772 --> 01:37:43,105
Olivia, have you noticed something?
奥莉维亚，你注意到了吗

1119
01:37:43,358 --> 01:37:45,598
That you're never taken to meet the begum and the ladies.
土邦王从来不带你去见女王和王妃们

1120
01:37:46,277 --> 01:37:48,109
I've met them, thank you.
我已经见过她们了，谢谢你

1121
01:37:49,405 --> 01:37:50,646
It was hard going.
挺煎熬的

1122
01:37:52,033 --> 01:37:54,867
Nevertheless, it's a discourtesy.
尽管如此，但这很失礼

1123
01:37:55,870 --> 01:37:58,032
- To whom?
对谁失礼？
- To you, to you my dear.
对你啊，亲爱的

1124
01:37:58,331 --> 01:38:01,199
Even had a quarrel with him about it, about you.
我和他为这事还吵了一架，关于你

1125
01:38:01,834 --> 01:38:03,496
- I asked him straight out.
我直接问他
- What?
什么？

1126
01:38:03,544 --> 01:38:06,912
Why don't take Olivia, Mrs Rivers, to meet the begum?
你为什么不带奥莉维亚里弗斯夫人见女王？

1127
01:38:07,548 --> 01:38:09,631
- And he...
然后他
- What?
他怎么了？

1128
01:38:10,510 --> 01:38:13,344
You know what he's like when he doesn't want to answer something.
你知道的，当他不想回答的时候，他就会这样

1129
01:38:13,388 --> 01:38:16,847
He laughs and if you keep on he makes you feel a fool and prim
笑呵呵的，如果你一直问，他会让你觉得自己像个傻子

1130
01:38:16,891 --> 01:38:19,053
and stupid for asking such a question.
问了一个愚蠢的问题

1131
01:38:20,311 --> 01:38:21,267
He's very good at that.
他很擅长伪装

1132
01:38:21,312 --> 01:38:24,271
But Harry, I don't want to meet the begum.
但是哈里，我不想去见女王

1133
01:38:25,024 --> 01:38:26,765
I can't be friends with her, can I?
我又不能和她成为朋友，不是吗

1134
01:38:26,818 --> 01:38:29,401
Not with someone who doesn't speak the same language.
你无法和一个语言不通的人成为朋友

1135
01:38:30,446 --> 01:38:33,689
I enjoy being here with you and him, of course.
我喜欢和你待在这儿，当然还有他

1136
01:38:34,033 --> 01:38:35,865
I mean, as your friend.
我是说，作为你们的朋友

1137
01:38:36,911 --> 01:38:38,322
We have a good time.
我们相处得很开心

1138
01:38:40,706 --> 01:38:43,870
Oh, don't look like that, Harry.
哦，哈里不要那个表情

1139
01:38:45,336 --> 01:38:49,250
Now you're being like everyone else making me feel I don't understand.
现在你看起来就像另外一个人，让我觉得我看不懂你

1140
01:38:49,757 --> 01:38:51,157
Olivia, shall I tell you something?
奥莉维亚，我能和你说实话吗？

1141
01:38:51,384 --> 01:38:53,376
I don't think you ought to be coming here.
我觉得你不该来这儿

1142
01:38:54,011 --> 01:38:56,378
In fact, I wish you wouldn't.
事实上，我希望你从来没来过

1143
01:38:56,514 --> 01:38:58,881
But Harry, I come to see you.
但是哈里，我是来看你的

1144
01:38:59,434 --> 01:39:02,393
Of course, naturally, me.
你当然是来看我的

1145
01:39:52,403 --> 01:39:53,644
You're awake.
你还没睡？

1146
01:39:54,989 --> 01:39:56,400
I saw your light.
我看见你房间的灯还亮着

1147
01:39:57,450 --> 01:39:59,612
It's bad for you to read this late.
这么晚看信对你眼睛不好

1148
01:40:17,303 --> 01:40:20,011
I suppose you want to be my very good friend again.
我猜你又想成为我非常好的朋友了

1149
01:40:20,306 --> 01:40:21,467
Do you mind?
你介意吗？

1150
01:40:33,903 --> 01:40:35,943
What a shock he'd have if he knew.
要是让他知道了，他会吓到的

1151
01:40:36,697 --> 01:40:38,108
I was due on the eighth,
我的生理期是8号

1152
01:40:39,283 --> 01:40:43,493
the 15th, the 22nd,
15号，22号

1153
01:40:44,830 --> 01:40:47,117
that's more than two weeks overdue, isn't that wonderful?
推迟了两周，不是什么好兆头吧？

1154
01:40:48,084 --> 01:40:50,292
It's my own fault, I should've taken care.
都是我的错，我应该小心一点儿的

1155
01:40:56,759 --> 01:40:58,170
Thinking again?
又在想事情？

1156
01:41:00,513 --> 01:41:04,223
On the contrary not thinking at all, just letting whatever happens happen.
恰恰相反，我什么都没想，就让一切顺其自然吧

1157
01:41:41,387 --> 01:41:43,549
Please wait for me here.
请在这儿等我

1158
01:42:10,249 --> 01:42:12,929
They still have that tent, Mrs Rivers
里弗斯夫人，他们现在仍然保留着那个帐篷

1159
01:42:12,960 --> 01:42:16,544
and the blood is so fresh and new it's as if it had only happened yesterday.
鲜红的血液，仿佛一切发生在昨天

1160
01:42:19,133 --> 01:42:21,671
- Oh.
哦
- Did you have a bad dream?
你做噩梦了？

1161
01:42:23,387 --> 01:42:25,219
- Are they gone?
他们走了？
- Who?
谁？

1162
01:42:26,349 --> 01:42:27,349
Those men.
那些男人

1163
01:42:29,602 --> 01:42:30,968
Who were they?
他们是谁？

1164
01:44:10,327 --> 01:44:12,990
I've told Maji about being pregnant.
我告诉玛姬我怀孕了

1165
01:44:13,247 --> 01:44:14,454
She's a midwife
她是个助产士

1166
01:44:14,790 --> 01:44:17,578
and said if I want an abortion she might try,
她告诉我，如果我想堕胎，她也许可以试一试

1167
01:44:17,668 --> 01:44:19,330
with just a massage.
只需要一次简单的按摩

1168
01:44:21,213 --> 01:44:23,375
I said "All right let's try".
我回答，好的，我们试一试

1169
01:44:25,426 --> 01:44:28,760
She said I was about seven weeks gone so it would be easy now.
她说我才怀孕七周，现在堕胎很容易。

1170
01:44:29,346 --> 01:44:31,554
She knew many ways, but at this stage
她知道很多种办法，但目前这个阶段

1171
01:44:31,724 --> 01:44:33,681
a simple massage could do it.
有一种简单的按摩方法

1172
01:45:20,731 --> 01:45:22,393
No, Maji, no, Maji, no.
不，玛姬，不玛姬，不要
1173
01:45:25,986 --> 01:45:27,852
I asked her over and over.
我一次又一次地问她

1174
01:45:28,280 --> 01:45:32,490
"You didn't really do anything, did you? Nothing will happen?"
你没有真的做什么，是吧？胎儿也没事，是吧？

1175
01:45:32,785 --> 01:45:36,028
And she assured me no, she didn't, "No, it wouldn't."
她向我保证，她什么都没做，胎儿没事

1176
01:45:37,581 --> 01:45:40,824
Then she asked me, "You want the child?"
接着她问我，你想留下这个孩子？

1177
01:45:41,961 --> 01:45:45,454
And I said, "Yes I do, I do."
我回答她，我想，我想要，我想要

1178
01:46:00,145 --> 01:46:02,478
Darling, Olivia, are you partaking?
亲爱的奥莉维亚，你喝酒吗？

1179
01:46:05,734 --> 01:46:07,020
- Major?
梅杰？
- Yes, please.
是的

1180
01:46:08,696 --> 01:46:09,696
Well.
好吧

1181
01:46:11,740 --> 01:46:15,700
To our charming hostess who has elected to stay with us
敬我们美丽的主人，在瘟疫爆发的时候

1182
01:46:15,744 --> 01:46:18,612
through our ordeal far down in the plague.
选择和我们一起共度难关

1183
01:46:18,956 --> 01:46:20,663
Yes, rather.
是的，非常勇敢。

1184
01:46:22,001 --> 01:46:23,001
Here, here.
干杯，干杯

1185
01:46:24,837 --> 01:46:27,545
But Major, aren't you due for a spot of leave in the hills?
但是梅杰，你不是要休假去山里避暑吗？

1186
01:46:27,923 --> 01:46:31,007
Yes, but this is not the time to go.
是的，但现在不是时候

1187
01:46:31,510 --> 01:46:34,127
Our friend the Nawab has been acting up again
我们的朋友土邦王又在挑事了

1188
01:46:34,179 --> 01:46:36,136
and I'm afraid things are coming to a head.
我怕事态会控制不住

1189
01:46:36,891 --> 01:46:39,474
At present I wouldn't like to be in that boy's shoes.
目前我还不太清楚这个家伙在打什么主意

1190
01:46:40,561 --> 01:46:41,561
Which boy's shoes?
哪个家伙？

1191
01:46:42,438 --> 01:46:43,519
Our friend.
我们的朋友

1192
01:46:44,398 --> 01:46:47,766
I trust Simla isn't gonna dillydally any further over him.
我相信他不会去西米拉那么远的地方消磨时光的

1193
01:46:48,736 --> 01:46:50,477
It's certainly time he was taught a lesson.
是时候给他点儿颜色看看了

1194
01:46:50,863 --> 01:46:52,570
You talk as if he's a school boy.
你说的好像他是个不听话的学生

1195
01:46:52,990 --> 01:46:55,824
Ah, I wish it were that harmless.
啊，我希望他不是个危险的学生

1196
01:46:56,410 --> 01:46:58,276
Olivia, he's a dangerous ruffian.
奥莉维亚，他是个危险的暴徒

1197
01:46:59,079 --> 01:47:01,947
Those dacoits of his are running around killing and maiming
他手下的那些强盗在他的保护下

1198
01:47:02,041 --> 01:47:04,078
with his blessing, under his protection.
四处残害良民

1199
01:47:05,127 --> 01:47:07,460
He's a menace to himself, to us,
他不仅对我们是个危险人物，对他自己

1200
01:47:08,213 --> 01:47:11,126
and to the wretched inhabitants of his wretched little state.
对那个可怜的国家，人民也是个危险人物

1201
01:47:11,216 --> 01:47:13,378
He's the worst sort of ruler.
他是最危险的统治者

1202
01:47:13,802 --> 01:47:16,169
The worst sort of Indian you could have.
可能是你见过的最危险的统治者

1203
01:47:22,227 --> 01:47:25,015
Dear lady, are you leaving us?
亲爱的女士，你要离开了吗？

1204
01:47:25,439 --> 01:47:27,556
To your brandy and cigars.
远离你们的白兰地和雪茄

1205
01:47:33,197 --> 01:47:34,654
She's very plucky.
她真的很勇敢

1206
01:47:35,074 --> 01:47:37,441
I believe it went up to 118 today.
我觉得今天的温度达到118华氏度了

1207
01:47:39,286 --> 01:47:41,198
All right Rivers, better go and see how she is.
里弗斯，没关系的，你还是去看看她吧

1208
01:47:41,455 --> 01:47:43,447
Will you mind, sir? I think I ought to.
先生们，失陪一下，我去看看她

1209
01:47:47,336 --> 01:47:49,828
So, they are setting up a committee of inquiry?
这么说，他们成立了一个调查委员会？

1210
01:47:50,506 --> 01:47:51,506
Yes.
是的

1211
01:47:52,341 --> 01:47:53,877
And I'm rather afraid...
恐怕他们打算

1212
01:47:55,135 --> 01:47:57,001
they'll be putting our Nawab out of business
把我们的土邦王踢出局

1213
01:47:57,096 --> 01:47:58,303
which is a pity,
真遗憾

1214
01:47:58,555 --> 01:48:00,672
because there's no denying he has a quality.
因为不可否认的是他本质不坏

1215
01:48:01,725 --> 01:48:02,841
He is a prince.
他可是个王子

1216
01:48:03,560 --> 01:48:07,395
Yes, but the trouble is, his little state isn't quite princely enough to satisfy him.
没错，问题是他那个小国家，不足以满足他王子般的需求

1217
01:48:08,482 --> 01:48:11,350
Poor fellow is tremendously bored.
可怜的家伙是太无聊了

1218
01:48:12,319 --> 01:48:14,982
I think he'd do anything to amuse himself.
我觉得他会做任何事愉悦自己

1219
01:48:20,119 --> 01:48:21,119
Olivia.
奥莉维亚

1220
01:48:29,044 --> 01:48:30,044
What is it?
你怎么了？

1221
01:48:32,506 --> 01:48:33,747
I ought to tell you.
我应该告诉你的

1222
01:48:35,175 --> 01:48:37,041
It isn't just the heat.
不仅是天气热的原因

1223
01:48:39,930 --> 01:48:41,466
What is it? Tell me.
那是什么，快告诉我

1224
01:48:41,932 --> 01:48:42,932
Are you ill?
你生病了吗？

1225
01:48:44,476 --> 01:48:45,476
Olivia.
奥莉维亚

1226
01:48:46,729 --> 01:48:50,769
The fact is, I'm pregnant.
其实，我怀孕了

1227
01:48:53,694 --> 01:48:54,694
Darling.
亲爱的

1228
01:48:56,238 --> 01:48:59,777
Darling, it's what we want, more than anything.
亲爱的，孩子 是我们最想要的

1229
01:49:02,119 --> 01:49:03,951
Yes, of course it is.
是的，当然了

1230
01:49:31,774 --> 01:49:33,561
Good morning.
早上好

1231
01:49:34,651 --> 01:49:37,519
I'll have to keep bringing more Dickens for Mr Hamilton-Paul.
我给汉密尔顿保罗先生又拿了几本狄更斯的书

1232
01:49:38,989 --> 01:49:40,776
We're on <i>Our Mutual Friend</i> now.
我们在看我们共同的朋友

1233
01:49:40,908 --> 01:49:41,908
Ah.
啊

1234
01:49:42,993 --> 01:49:45,360
He can't seem to get enough of foggy London...
他似乎欣赏不够伦敦的雾色

1235
01:49:45,412 --> 01:49:47,495
...and Christmas revels.
和圣诞的狂欢

1236
01:49:48,582 --> 01:49:52,166
- Isn't it extraordinary?
是不是很奇怪
- Yes indeed, extraordinary.
是的，确实很奇怪

1237
01:49:59,593 --> 01:50:03,428
It was all so murky, both sides intriguing.
一切都是暗箱操作，双方都在密谋策划

1238
01:50:03,764 --> 01:50:07,804
The British too, they were playing their own game,
英国人也一样，他们只想参与属于他们自己的游戏

1239
01:50:08,143 --> 01:50:09,475
they always did.
他们一向如此

1240
01:50:10,479 --> 01:50:14,598
They'd set up some sort of committee to depose him.
他们成立了某种委员会罢黜了他

1241
01:50:15,609 --> 01:50:19,728
"Put him out of business" was the facetious phrase they used.
他们的官方术语是踢出局，很滑稽

1242
01:50:22,491 --> 01:50:28,112
And, for his successor, they'd picked out some halfwit,
他们任命了他妹妹的儿子

1243
01:50:28,789 --> 01:50:30,200
epileptic nephew.
那个患有癫痫症的傻外甥

1244
01:50:31,208 --> 01:50:33,871
He was the son of the Nawab's sister.
继承王位

1245
01:50:34,670 --> 01:50:38,289
That of course was because the Nawab had no son of his own.
当然也是因为土邦王自己没有子嗣

1246
01:50:39,716 --> 01:50:41,799
As it turned out in the end
结果我最后

1247
01:50:41,885 --> 01:50:46,550
it was more convenient to drop the nephew than simply to swallow up the whole state
罢黜这个外甥提供了便利，轻而易举地将整个国家

1248
01:50:46,598 --> 01:50:48,590
into British India.
纳入英国殖民的印度地区

1249
01:50:49,643 --> 01:50:52,727
How dare they appoint anyone to inquire into my activities.
他们怎敢派人调查我的行踪？

1250
01:50:53,230 --> 01:50:55,643
I told him. I told your Major Minnies.
我告诉他了，告诉你的梅杰・明尼

1251
01:50:55,732 --> 01:50:56,732
Why mine?
为什么是我的？

1252
01:50:57,693 --> 01:51:00,026
No, of course not, you have nothing to do with it.
不，当然不是你的，和你一点儿关系都没有

1253
01:51:00,571 --> 01:51:04,906
Anyway I made it very clear that from now I shall deal with the viceroy, personally.
不管怎样，我表明了我的态度，从现在起，我要亲自和总督交涉

1254
01:51:05,367 --> 01:51:06,608
I told him.
我和他说了

1255
01:51:06,743 --> 01:51:08,735
I don't deal with underlings Major Minnies.
我不喜欢梅杰・明尼这群党羽

1256
01:51:09,329 --> 01:51:10,865
I know what this is all about.
我知道这一切是为了什么

1257
01:51:10,956 --> 01:51:16,122
I know why they hate me, because I don't say, "Yes, Your Excellency."
我知道他们为什么恨我，因为我不说，阁下，遵命

1258
01:51:16,378 --> 01:51:17,914
"Very good, Your Excellency."
非常好，阁下

1259
01:51:18,005 --> 01:51:19,792
"How right and true, Your Excellency."
你说的没错，阁下

1260
01:51:19,840 --> 01:51:21,206
I have something to tell you.
我有个消息要告诉你

1261
01:51:21,383 --> 01:51:22,383
What is it?
什么消息？

1262
01:51:25,596 --> 01:51:27,929
What is it? Tell me.
什么消息？告诉我

1263
01:51:30,142 --> 01:51:31,258
Can't you guess?
你不能猜猜吗？

1264
01:51:34,521 --> 01:51:35,602
I'm pregnant.
我怀孕了

1265
01:51:53,248 --> 01:51:54,989
You're made to bear a child.
你注定要怀孕的

1266
01:51:57,961 --> 01:51:59,202
Are you afraid?
你害怕吗？

1267
01:52:02,007 --> 01:52:03,373
Don't be afraid.
别害怕

1268
01:52:06,011 --> 01:52:07,377
Now they'll see.
现在他们等着瞧吧

1269
01:52:08,972 --> 01:52:12,306
- Who'll see?
谁？
- Major Minnies and the rest of them.
梅杰・明尼还有其他人

1270
01:52:13,644 --> 01:52:15,806
They'll laugh out of the other sides of their mouths
当他们见到我儿子的时候

1271
01:52:15,854 --> 01:52:17,345
when they see my son.
会笑的前仰后合

1272
01:52:18,315 --> 01:52:20,728
Do you mean because...
你的意思是……

1273
01:52:21,902 --> 01:52:23,109
of the colour?
肤色的原因吗？

1274
01:52:23,195 --> 01:52:26,484
Oh, they'll get the shock of their little English lives.
哦，他们会为这个英国小生命而震惊的

1275
01:52:27,491 --> 01:52:28,491
No, no.
不，不

1276
01:52:29,785 --> 01:52:31,026
You mustn't go.
你不能离开

1277
01:52:33,288 --> 01:52:36,122
I want you to stay here, you must.
我希望你留下来，你必须留下来

1278
01:52:37,084 --> 01:52:40,168
My son must be born here in my house.
我的儿子必须在我的房子里出生

1279
01:52:41,672 --> 01:52:43,459
How can you be so sure?
你怎么能这么肯定呢？

1280
01:52:44,633 --> 01:52:47,467
I'm very sure, absolutely.
我就是很肯定，非常确定

1281
01:52:48,262 --> 01:52:49,298
He's mine.
他就是我的儿子

1282
01:52:50,597 --> 01:52:52,088
He couldn't not be.
不可能是别人的

1283
01:52:52,891 --> 01:52:53,927
What about Douglas?
道格拉斯呢？

1284
01:52:57,187 --> 01:53:01,602
He's as sure as you are, and he's my husband.
他和你一样肯定，他还是我的丈夫

1285
01:53:10,867 --> 01:53:12,324
What have I done?
我都做了什么？

1286
01:53:14,913 --> 01:53:16,324
What have I done?
我都做了什么？

1287
01:53:23,505 --> 01:53:25,588
What have <i>you</i> made me do?
你都让我做了什么？

1288
01:53:40,397 --> 01:53:42,605
How do you know it'll be a he?
你怎么知道是个男孩儿呢

1289
01:53:43,191 --> 01:53:44,523
Oh, I'm pretty sure.
我非常确定

1290
01:53:45,736 --> 01:53:48,149
And he'll do something decent too, you'll see.
你看着吧，他将来会从事非常体面的工作

1291
01:53:49,823 --> 01:53:53,442
I must ask my sister to send the Rivers' christening robe.
我要让我姐姐把里弗斯家的洗礼长袍寄过来

1292
01:53:54,202 --> 01:53:56,194
All the Rivers babies are christened in it.
里弗斯家的孩子都是穿着它接受洗礼的

1293
01:53:58,749 --> 01:54:00,081
You know, they're all very blond.
你知道的，他们都是金发碧眼

1294
01:54:01,126 --> 01:54:03,584
We all have white blond hair 'til we're about 12.
十二岁以前，我们的头发都是银色的

1295
01:54:07,382 --> 01:54:08,623
Look, I'm sorry.
听着，我很抱歉

1296
01:54:10,260 --> 01:54:12,593
What a stupid ass I am to bring you here.
我是个笨蛋，竟然带你来这儿

1297
01:54:14,181 --> 01:54:15,888
We won't come back again.
我们再也不来这儿了

1298
01:54:17,434 --> 01:54:18,720
Come on darling, let's go.
亲爱的，别哭了，我们走吧

1299
01:54:38,080 --> 01:54:40,037
I can hardly find an abortionist for you.
我找不到一个能帮你堕胎的人

1300
01:54:40,374 --> 01:54:42,616
Ask your friends in the purdah quarters.
问问你那些营房里的朋友

1301
01:54:44,795 --> 01:54:46,002
Ask the begum.
还有女王

1302
01:54:47,381 --> 01:54:49,589
It'll be easy enough for her.
对她来讲，轻而易举

1303
01:54:53,220 --> 01:54:56,759
Easier than poisoned garments any day.
比用衣服毒死人容易多了

1304
01:55:01,770 --> 01:55:03,511
I couldn't refuse her.
我无法拒绝她

1305
01:55:03,855 --> 01:55:07,064
I didn't want to see this baby born any more than she did.
我和她一样不想这个孩子出生

1306
01:55:07,526 --> 01:55:11,645
No one did, except the Nawab and Douglas.
没人想，除了土邦王和道格拉斯

1307
01:55:13,990 --> 01:55:16,027
The begum was glad to help.
女王非常愿意帮忙

1308
01:55:16,326 --> 01:55:19,740
She wanted no complications with the British on the one hand
她既不想跟英国扯上关系，也不想

1309
01:55:19,913 --> 01:55:23,532
nor did she fancy a little Eurasian heir.
有一个欧亚混血的继承人

1310
01:55:23,917 --> 01:55:27,160
Of course, there had to be the utmost secrecy
当然这是最高机密

1311
01:55:27,379 --> 01:55:29,541
because if the Nawab had ever found out
因为一旦被土邦王发现了

1312
01:55:29,756 --> 01:55:31,748
he'd have killed someone.
他会杀了所有人

1313
01:55:31,883 --> 01:55:35,467
He believed 'til the end that it was a natural miscarriage.
一直到最后，他都相信是自然流产

1314
01:56:06,501 --> 01:56:08,959
She had begun to bleed the same night
当晚她就开始流血

1315
01:56:09,045 --> 01:56:10,752
and Douglas took her to the hospital.
道格拉斯带她去了医院

1316
01:56:11,673 --> 01:56:13,505
Well, my young madam.
我可怜的女士

1317
01:56:14,593 --> 01:56:17,711
But Dr Saunders was all too familiar with the methods
但桑德斯医生非常熟悉

1318
01:56:17,804 --> 01:56:21,093
used by Indian midwives to procure abortions.
印度助产士的堕胎手段

1319
01:56:23,393 --> 01:56:26,101
I never knew how she got from the hospital to the palace.
我一直都不知道她是如何从医院逃到皇宫的

1320
01:56:26,813 --> 01:56:28,475
A distance of nine miles.
那可是九英里的距离

1321
01:56:28,940 --> 01:56:31,683
And she could hardly have walked it in the middle of the night
她刚堕胎，失血过多，那种状态几乎不可能

1322
01:56:31,776 --> 01:56:36,020
and her condition with all that loss of blood from her abortion.
在半夜里行走

1323
01:56:37,240 --> 01:56:40,654
She'd borrowed some servant's sari in the hospital.
她在医院向一个仆人借来纱丽

1324
01:56:41,119 --> 01:56:43,907
She reminded me of one of those mutiny prints.
这让我想起了当时的一则暴乱新闻

1325
01:56:44,748 --> 01:56:49,334
I think it's called "Mrs Secombe In Flight from the Mutineers".
我记得一名叫斯科姆太太的女人从暴徒手中逃了出来

1326
01:56:50,253 --> 01:56:52,495
Now Mrs Secombe was also in native dress
当时斯科姆太太穿着本地服装

1327
01:56:52,547 --> 01:56:54,254
and in a state of agitation.
焦虑不安

1328
01:56:55,091 --> 01:56:56,798
Olivia was in flight as well,
奥莉维亚也是一样的

1329
01:56:57,260 --> 01:57:00,048
but of course, in the opposite direction,
只不过是逃往了相反的方向

1330
01:57:00,722 --> 01:57:02,839
from the civil station at Satipur
从赛提普的中心医院

1331
01:57:02,933 --> 01:57:04,970
to the Nawab's palace at Khatm.
逃到了土邦王的哈塔姆皇宫

1332
01:57:30,293 --> 01:57:32,285
Chid, you look absolutely awful.
奇德，你看起来糟透了

1333
01:57:32,921 --> 01:57:34,412
I think I'm gonna die.
我想我快死了

1334
01:57:37,968 --> 01:57:39,084
His liver's affected.
他的肝和肾
1335
01:57:42,389 --> 01:57:44,722
And his kidneys too, sit up.
都被感染了，坐起来

1336
01:57:47,060 --> 01:57:48,141
What does he expect?
他在想什么

1337
01:57:48,645 --> 01:57:51,353
Even I wouldn't think of eating and living the way he has done.
即使我也不能想象像他那样的吃饭和生活

1338
01:57:55,277 --> 01:57:57,769
My prescription for him is to put him on the next plane home
我给他的建议是马上乘飞机回家

1339
01:57:57,821 --> 01:57:59,403
and the sooner the better.
越快越好

1340
01:58:03,827 --> 01:58:07,946
My dear young man, your body's not made to live the life of a holy man.
亲爱的年轻人，你的身体不是让你以圣人的方式生活的
  
1341
01:58:10,458 --> 01:58:12,541
Psst. Let's go.
嘘，我们走吧

1342
01:58:14,546 --> 01:58:16,253
What about you, when are you going?
你呢，打算什么时候离开？

1343
01:58:17,340 --> 01:58:19,423
Don't know, I haven't made any plans.
不知道，我还没有计划

1344
01:58:19,467 --> 01:58:20,958
When my money runs out I suppose.
也许等我没钱的时候吧

1345
01:58:21,886 --> 01:58:24,970
I'm staying with my Aunt Betty in Iowa, Washington Iowa.
我会和爱荷华州的贝蒂阿姨住在一起，华盛顿的爱荷华州

1346
01:58:25,515 --> 01:58:27,552
It's the cleanest city in the whole USA.
那是全美国最干净的城市

1347
01:58:27,934 --> 01:58:29,800
It's a fact, it won a prize for it.
事实上，它还因此得过奖

1348
01:58:31,605 --> 01:58:33,221
You should see my Aunt Betty's bathroom.
你们应该去看看我阿姨贝蒂的卫生间

1349
01:58:33,648 --> 01:58:37,688
Everything matches, the shower curtain, the bath mat, the toilet paper,
一切都搭配得体，浴帘，防滑垫，厕纸

1350
01:58:37,902 --> 01:58:39,894
the little woolly cover on the toilet seat.
甚至是马桶座上的小木盖

1351
01:58:42,198 --> 01:58:43,734
Everything's green.
一切都是绿色的

1352
01:58:44,492 --> 01:58:45,733
Clean fresh green.
干净清新的绿色

1353
01:58:46,244 --> 01:58:47,610
Have a safe journey.
一路平安

1354
01:58:47,829 --> 01:58:51,698
If you think the bathrooms clean, you ought to see the kitchen!
要是你觉得卫生间很干净，那你该去看看厨房

1355
01:58:52,334 --> 01:58:55,202
- Take care.
保重
- Everything's clean fresh green!
一切都是干净清新的绿色

1356
01:58:55,378 --> 01:58:59,167
Goodbye, Chid, bye bye.
拜拜，奇德，拜拜

1357
01:59:19,903 --> 01:59:22,441
I knew she was rotten from the first day I saw her.
我第一天见到太多的时候就发现他不简单

1358
01:59:22,530 --> 01:59:25,113
Well she wasn't a bad sort, just the wrong type to come out here.
但她不是那种坏人，只不过看起来像坏人

1359
01:59:25,367 --> 01:59:27,324
Her embroidery and her piano.
她会刺绣和弹钢琴

1360
01:59:27,702 --> 01:59:30,035
That's all very nice at home, it'll hardly due for Satipur.
家里的陈设很干净，但到了赛提普就不一样了

1361
01:59:31,122 --> 01:59:32,784
She killed her own baby.
她杀死了自己的孩子

1362
01:59:33,208 --> 01:59:36,497
- Oh come, come, Joan.
琼，别这么说
- She could have a baby,
她可以留下这个孩子的

1363
01:59:36,628 --> 01:59:37,664
and she killed it.
但她堕掉了

1364
01:59:37,921 --> 01:59:40,664
Don't forget, my dear, whose baby it was.
亲爱的，不要忘了那是谁的孩子

1365
01:59:40,840 --> 01:59:42,706
What does that matter as long as...
那有什么关系呢，只要……

1366
01:59:44,344 --> 01:59:45,926
as long as she cared for him?
只要她在乎他

1367
01:59:46,846 --> 01:59:49,839
I just can't stop thinking about it.
我只是忍不住去想这个孩子

1368
01:59:53,186 --> 01:59:55,428
Come along, Joan, it's time I got you home.
琼，过来，我们该回家了

1369
01:59:56,940 --> 01:59:58,306
Bed for you, my dear.
亲爱的贝德福特

1370
01:59:59,025 --> 02:00:00,311
Those are doctor's orders.
谨遵医嘱

1371
02:00:00,360 --> 02:00:03,023
- Goodnight, goodnight.
晚安
- Goodnight Joan.
晚安，琼

1372
02:00:03,279 --> 02:00:04,941
Now you take good care of yourself, Joan.
好好照顾自己，琼

1373
02:00:05,198 --> 02:00:06,814
I will, thank you.
我会的，谢谢你

1374
02:00:06,950 --> 02:00:09,158
- Goodnight.
晚安
- Night.
晚安

1375
02:00:14,791 --> 02:00:19,627
Well, she may have cared for him, but I don't think that your precious Nawab
好吧，她可能在乎他，但我觉得你那位尊贵的土邦王
1376
02:00:19,671 --> 02:00:20,957
has returned the compliment.
回绝了她的关心

1377
02:00:21,005 --> 02:00:24,248
What a bounder to have taken his revenge in that way.
以这种方式进行报复，他也太残忍了

1378
02:00:24,342 --> 02:00:27,631
- Was it only revenge?
仅仅是报复吗？
- Do you doubt it?
你不这么认为吗？

1379
02:00:28,930 --> 02:00:31,297
No, I suppose not, not really.
不，我不这么认为

1380
02:00:32,684 --> 02:00:33,925
How is Rivers taking it?
里弗斯怎么样了

1381
02:00:34,561 --> 02:00:36,302
Like a Stoic and a Roman.
既像一个禁欲者又像一个罗马人

1382
02:00:36,688 --> 02:00:38,429
He's a splendid chap.
他是个了不起的家伙

1383
02:00:38,690 --> 02:00:41,290
I've sent him on tour to get him away from this place for a while.
我派遣他外出了，暂时离开这里一段时间

1384
02:00:41,901 --> 02:00:43,392
He picked the wrong girl.
他选错了伴侣

1385
02:00:44,529 --> 02:00:46,862
I'm so immensely fond of him, I wish I could...
我非常了解他，我希望他能

1386
02:00:47,615 --> 02:00:49,527
What, match-making already?
什么，已经开始做媒了？

1387
02:00:49,909 --> 02:00:52,196
Oh, my dear man, that's what a burra memsahib's for.
哦，亲爱的，我可是善意的

1388
02:00:54,706 --> 02:00:55,867
Poor Olivia.
可怜的奥莉维亚

1389
02:00:57,917 --> 02:00:59,658
She was a fine looking girl, too.
她曾经长得很漂亮

1390
02:01:00,253 --> 02:01:02,745
Was? She's not dead.
曾经？她又没去世

1391
02:01:03,840 --> 02:01:05,251
As good as.
最好是这样

1392
02:02:53,324 --> 02:02:55,684
The Chowkidar told me that a long time ago
这个看房子的男人告诉我，很久以前

1393
02:02:55,743 --> 02:02:57,325
an English memsahib lived here.
有一个英国女人住在这里

1394
02:02:58,121 --> 02:03:01,455
She lived completely alone, then she died.
一直孤身一人，直到去世

1395
02:03:02,584 --> 02:03:04,416
That was 20 or 30 years ago.
大概二三十年以前的样子吧

1396
02:03:05,378 --> 02:03:07,916
Now the house belongs to the Nawab's great nephew
现在这个房子属于土邦王的甥孙

1397
02:03:08,298 --> 02:03:09,880
who's a general in the Indian army.
现在掌管印度的军队

1398
02:03:10,800 --> 02:03:12,917
He comes here every summer with his family.
他每年夏天都和家人来这里

1399
02:03:31,988 --> 02:03:35,322
He came out to see her about two or three times a year.
他大概一年去看她两三次

1400
02:03:35,783 --> 02:03:37,900
The rest of the time he was mostly in London
剩下的大多数时间都在伦敦

1401
02:03:38,036 --> 02:03:40,824
trying to get his deposition annulled.
试图取消他的罢黜

1402
02:03:41,164 --> 02:03:43,201
His mother came to live in London, too.
他的妈妈也去了伦敦

1403
02:03:43,875 --> 02:03:47,118
She bought a house in Park Lane, which they've since pulled down.
在公园路买了一处房子，罢黜后他们一直住在那里

1404
02:03:48,838 --> 02:03:52,252
It was said that she'd taken the state jewels with her,
据说她带走了国家的珠宝

1405
02:03:52,759 --> 02:03:54,216
but it could never be proved,
但无从考证

1406
02:03:54,594 --> 02:03:57,132
nor could they get a single pearl away from her.
他们也没从她身上找到一件珠宝

1407
02:03:57,805 --> 02:04:00,889
They tried to bring a case against her, but to no avail.
他们想起诉她，但被判无效

1408
02:04:01,517 --> 02:04:04,385
Except every time a summons came,
不过每次传票来的时候

1409
02:04:04,479 --> 02:04:07,062
the Nawab got himself worked up.
土邦王都会非常暴躁

1410
02:04:07,148 --> 02:04:09,310
He'd roar and stamp around.
跺着脚，怒吼着

1411
02:04:10,360 --> 02:04:16,357
Then one day, quite suddenly, in his mother's flat, just like that.
后来有一天，在他母亲的公寓里，非常地突然，他就那样去世了

1412
02:04:18,660 --> 02:04:19,970
I don't know how long it was
我不知道过了多久

1413
02:04:19,994 --> 02:04:22,987
before news reached her that he wouldn't be coming anymore.
她才得知，他再也不会来看她了

1414
02:04:24,540 --> 02:04:26,953
Even after she knew, she never went down again
即便她知道了，她也没有下山

1415
02:04:27,001 --> 02:04:29,744
but stayed by herself in the house he had bought for her.
而是一个人生活在他给她买的房子里

1416
02:05:22,640 --> 02:05:23,847
Namaste.
修道院

1417
02:05:27,061 --> 02:05:28,518
The monastery?
修道院？

1418
02:05:28,938 --> 02:05:31,976
Would you like me to take you over there?
我带你过去怎么样？

1419
02:05:32,025 --> 02:05:33,106
Are you going?
你也去修道院？

1420
02:05:33,151 --> 02:05:35,234
- Yes, I am going there.
是的，我要去
- Thank you.
谢谢你

1421
02:05:35,319 --> 02:05:36,981
May I help you to...
我帮你拿背包吧

1422
02:05:42,035 --> 02:05:44,013
They have a little hospital up here.
这上面有个小医院

1423
02:05:44,037 --> 02:05:46,654
That's where Olivia went in the end.
那就是奥莉维亚最后去的意愿

1424
02:05:46,998 --> 02:05:49,490
They've agreed to let me come there for my baby.
他们同意我在这儿生下我的宝宝

